Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.31,0:06:37.81,Default-3,,0,0,0,,马蒂·安德森第一次看到那广告牌那天\N{\rEng}The day Marty Anderson first saw the billboard
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.83,0:06:43.21,Default-3,,0,0,0,,恰巧就在互联网彻底瘫痪前\N{\rEng}was just before the internet finally went down for good.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.75,0:06:46.19,Default-3,,0,0,0,,在那之前网时好时坏有八个月了\N{\rEng}It had been wobbling for eight months,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.28,0:06:49.69,Default-3,,0,0,0,,但占据头条的是其他事件\N{\rEng}but other problems, like fires, earthquakes,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.71,0:06:54.48,Default-3,,0,0,0,,像是大火 地震 鸟和鱼的彻底灭绝\N{\rEng}and whole species of birds and fish dying off had taken priority.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.50,0:06:59.55,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an9\i1}...烧到现在 这成为美国史上最严重的山火\N{\rEng}{\i1}...till today, thought to be the largest wildfire in United States history.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.38,0:07:08.45,Default-3,,0,0,0,,在过去 马蒂会直接走收费公路\N{\rEng}Ordinarily, Marty would've driven by way of the Turnpike bypass,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.47,0:07:15.53,Default-3,,0,0,0,,但自奥特溪桥塌了后那条路就走不通了\N{\rEng}but that wasn't possible due to the collapse of the bridge over Otter Creek.
