Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.37,0:07:36.24,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an9\i1}由于加州最近的灾难\N{\rEng}{\i1}Well, with what happened in California,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.33,0:07:39.68,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an9\i1}内华达州现在是全美人口最多的州\N{\rEng}{\i1}that officially makes Nevada one of the most populous states in the Union now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.76,0:07:41.33,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an9\i1}但需要强调的是...\N{\rEng}{\i1}The thing that must be said here is...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.42,0:07:44.95,Default-3,,0,0,0,,菲莉西娅·戈登是市立医院的护士\N{\rEng}Felicia Gordon is a nurse at City General.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.03,0:07:50.36,Default-3,,0,0,0,,最近几周她却更像是名收殓员\N{\rEng}Though for the last few weeks, she's felt more like an undertaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.38,0:07:54.68,Default-3,,0,0,0,,自夏末以来员工就不断的辞职\N{\rEng}The staff, whose numbers have been dwindling since late summer,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.71,0:07:59.84,Default-3,,0,0,0,,大家给自己起名叫“自杀小队”\N{\rEng}have begun referring to themselves as the Suicide Squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.91,0:08:00.81,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an9\i1}稍事休息\N{\rEng}{\i1}We'll be back to talk more about this
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.83,0:08:06.52,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an9\i1}稍后将带来中西部大火和缺水的最新情况\N{\rEng}{\i1}and, uh, also about the fires in the Midwest, speaking of water scarcity, back after this break.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.53,0:08:16.78,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an9\i1}感谢查尔斯·查克·克兰兹39年来的非凡岁月\N{\rEng}{\i1}We'd like to say thank you to Charles Krantz for 39 great years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.80,0:08:19.04,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an9\i1}谢谢你 查克\N{\rEng}{\i1}Thanks, Chuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.94,0:08:23.02,Default-3,,0,0,0,,嘿\N{\rEng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.20,0:08:25.44,Default-3,,0,0,0,,听说你又救了一个？\N{\rEng}Heard you got another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.46,0:08:27.08,Default-3,,0,0,0,,嗯 又一个\N{\rEng}Yeah. One more.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.16,0:08:30.27,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我的没那么幸运 手腕都割烂了 你懂的\N{\rEng}Mine wasn't so lucky. Slit wrists, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.29,0:08:32.25,Default-3,,0,0,0,,真没办法了\N{\rEng}what were we supposed to do really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.34,0:08:33.95,Default-3,,0,0,0,,听说玛丽露的事了吗？\N{\rEng}Hear about Marilou?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.04,0:08:35.69,Default-3,,0,0,0,,没 怎么了？\N{\rEng}No. What about Marilou?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.78,0:08:36.91,Default-3,,0,0,0,,她不干了\N{\rEng}She left!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.52,0:08:39.63,Default-3,,0,0,0,,-还记得她前任佩德罗吗？ -记得 \N{\rEng}-Her ex. Remember Pedro? -Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.65,0:08:41.61,Default-3,,0,0,0,,他冒出来 嘟囔了几句\N{\rEng}He showed up, and I don't know what he said to her,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.61,0:08:44.20,Default-3,,0,0,0,,两人牵着手就走了\N{\rEng}but she walked out holding his hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.22,0:08:45.94,Default-3,,0,0,0,,他们离婚离的有多难熬\N{\rEng}And I remember how bad that divorce was.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.96,0:08:47.66,Default-3,,0,0,0,,-有印象吗？ -嗯 记得 \N{\rEng}-Do you remember? -Yeah, I remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.74,0:08:51.99,Default-3,,0,0,0,,好吧 往事如烟了 他们又拉上了手\N{\rEng}Well, I guess that's all bridge water 'cause off she went.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.36,0:08:52.80,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an9\i1}...地陷不断出现\N{\rEng}{\i1}...sinkholes that have been opening up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.88,0:08:54.34,Default-3,,0,0,0,,现在婚姻都咋样？\N{\rEng}I wonder what the stats are.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.36,0:08:58.74,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是分居多还是复合多？\N{\rEng}You think more people are splitting up or getting back together?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.76,0:09:01.08,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是结婚多还是离婚多？\N{\rEng}I mean, do you think marriage rates are up or divorce rates...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.10,0:09:02.77,Default-3,,0,0,0,,结婚多\N{\rEng}Marriages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.98,0:09:05.00,Default-3,,0,0,0,,-你是个乐天派 -不 \N{\rEng}-You're an optimist. -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.63,0:09:08.70,Default-3,,0,0,0,,离婚周期长 没人会去排这个队\N{\rEng}Divorce takes way longer, and I don't think anyone's filing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.72,0:09:11.92,Default-3,,0,0,0,,填文件就得半年多 何苦呢？\N{\rEng}Why bother? Six months of paperwork at least. Probably more.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.94,0:09:15.43,Default-3,,0,0,0,,结婚领证上下只要一小时\N{\rEng}Marriage license is one page and it takes an hour or so.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.47,0:09:18.23,Default-3,,0,0,0,,所以我猜结婚多\N{\rEng}I'm gonna guess marriages.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.69,0:09:20.22,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}午餐不见你 晚餐也不在\N{\rEng}{\i1}Missed you for lunch, missed you for dinner.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.93,0:09:24.69,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(340,46)\fs13} 电影《封面女郎》(1944)
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.30,0:09:21.87,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}怎么了？辟谷了吗？\N{\rEng}{\i1}What's the matter? Don't you eat anymore?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.95,0:09:23.61,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}好吧 我不饿\N{\rEng}{\i1}Well, I wasn't hungry tonight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.69,0:09:25.18,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}那你今早也不饿吗？\N{\rEng}{\i1}Weren't you hungry this morning either?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.26,0:09:29.49,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}谁拿了我的舞蹈袜？天哪 谁那么坏\N{\rEng}{\i1}Who stole my nylons? Egads! The very...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.19,0:09:28.18,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(99,76)\frz22\fs9\b1\1c&HAFB349&}菲莉西娅·戈登来电
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.49,0:09:30.18,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}不饿\N{\rEng}{\i1}Not very.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.27,0:09:32.50,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}昨晚排练到很晚吗？\N{\rEng}{\i1}Too much rehearsal last night, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:32.53,0:09:33.94,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}就像锻炼一样\N{\rEng}{\i1}It was kind of a workout.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.96,0:09:35.73,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}赖床了？所以今早来的那么晚\N{\rEng}{\i1}That why you slept late?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.76,0:09:36.76,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}我可没晚起\N{\rEng}{\i1}Oh, I didn't sleep late.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.79,0:09:37.99,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}我去了富人区\N{\rEng}{\i1}I went uptown.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.01,0:09:40.30,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}-去购物？ -不是 \N{\rEng}{\i1}-Shopping? -No.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.71,0:09:43.71,Default-3,,0,0,0,,喂\N{\rEng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.67,0:09:46.87,Default-3,,0,0,0,,喂\N{\rEng}Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.33,0:09:50.77,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你给挂了？\N{\rEng}You hung up?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.85,0:09:52.20,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.68,0:09:55.40,Default-3,,0,0,0,,但后来想你看的到 所以又...\N{\rEng}But then I figured you probably saw it. So...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.03,0:09:58.03,Default-3,,0,0,0,,还好吗？\N{\rEng}How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.77,0:10:00.60,Default-3,,0,0,0,,还行吧\N{\rEng}I'm okay, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.69,0:10:01.78,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你呢？\N{\rEng}How are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.47,0:10:05.65,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我上班时想到你了\N{\rEng}I was, um, thinking about you today.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.68,0:10:09.46,Default-3,,0,0,0,,当时在猜结婚多还是离婚多\N{\rEng}We were at work talking about marriages and divorces. Like, which are happening more now...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.48,0:10:11.48,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我赌结婚多\N{\rEng}Marriages, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.65,0:10:13.84,Default-3,,0,0,0,,没人愿意等离婚\N{\rEng}Ain't nobody waiting on a divorce.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.27,0:10:16.47,Default-3,,0,0,0,,那么再婚呢？\N{\rEng}What about remarriages?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.75,0:10:19.42,Default-3,,0,0,0,,要约炮得先请我喝酒\N{\rEng}You want to buy a guy a drink first or...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.44,0:10:20.77,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我打赌人们都在再复合\N{\rEng}I bet those are happening.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.79,0:10:22.63,Default-3,,0,0,0,,这很有意义\N{\rEng}I mean, it makes sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.71,0:10:28.15,Default-3,,0,0,0,,人们现在渴望慰藉和熟悉的事物\N{\rEng}People wanting something comforting and familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.98,0:10:31.76,Default-3,,0,0,0,,那么 你今天过得怎么样？\N{\rEng}So... how was your day?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.29,0:10:34.74,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你想复合的意图太明显了 不觉得吗？\N{\rEng}You're just going right for it, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.76,0:10:36.02,Default-3,,0,0,0,,陪我聊聊\N{\rEng}Humor me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.20,0:10:41.99,Default-3,,0,0,0,,呃 今天就那样\N{\rEng}It was, um...It was a day, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.08,0:10:44.69,Default-3,,0,0,0,,有点怪\N{\rEng}You know? Weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.21,0:10:49.35,Default-3,,0,0,0,,家长会开的就像对牛弹琴\N{\rEng}Parent-teacher sessions, felt like pissing in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.56,0:10:51.02,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你听说加州的事儿了吧？\N{\rEng}You know about California, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.04,0:10:52.79,Default-3,,0,0,0,,听说了\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.87,0:10:54.46,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我听说大部分人都迁移了\N{\rEng}I know they're saying most of it was already evacuated,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.48,0:10:57.94,Default-3,,0,0,0,,今天就有几十万灾民东迁\N{\rEng}but I heard today there are hundreds of thousands of refugees trekking east.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.96,0:11:00.73,Default-3,,0,0,0,,知道现在内华达州是全美人口最多的州吗？\N{\rEng}Did you know Nevada is one of the most  populous states in the Union now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.75,0:11:05.71,Default-3,,0,0,0,,听国家电台科学家说 加州就跟烂墙皮一样往下掉\N{\rEng}I heard a, a scientist on NPR say California is peeling away like old wallpaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.71,0:11:08.90,Default-3,,0,0,0,,今天下午 日本又有一座核电站被淹\N{\rEng}And another Japanese reactor got inundated this afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.93,0:11:11.22,Default-3,,0,0,0,,他们虽说 停机了 一切安全\N{\rEng}And they're saying, you know, it was shut down and all's well,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.24,0:11:13.19,Default-3,,0,0,0,,但我就是没法相信\N{\rEng}but I just, I, I don't think I believe that.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.24,0:11:15.41,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你真是个怀疑论者\N{\rEng}Cynic.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.44,0:11:18.33,Default-3,,0,0,0,,好吧 马蒂 这日子就是这么不靠谱\N{\rEng}Well, we're living in cynical times, Marty.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.36,0:11:21.01,Default-3,,0,0,0,,不少人都认为天要塌了\N{\rEng}I mean, some people think we're living in the last times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.03,0:11:23.18,Default-3,,0,0,0,,不再是邪教成员这样想了\N{\rEng}Not just the religious crazies either. Not anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.20,0:11:29.28,Default-3,,0,0,0,,市立医院自杀小队的许多专家也这样说\N{\rEng}And you are hearing that from a member in good standing of the City General Suicide Squad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.30,0:11:30.58,Default-3,,0,0,0,,那是我们的自称\N{\rEng}That's what we call ourselves now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.60,0:11:32.18,Default-3,,0,0,0,,可没瞎说\N{\rEng}No lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.34,0:11:36.89,Default-3,,0,0,0,,今天有6人没挺过来 但救回了18人 主要用纳洛酮\N{\rEng}We lost six today, but there's 18 more we dragged back, mostly with naloxone.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.91,0:11:38.50,Default-3,,0,0,0,,但这种药已经供不上了\N{\rEng}But supplies of that are getting very thin.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.52,0:11:43.40,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我听药房说最多坚持到月底\N{\rEng}And I heard the head pharmacist say we might be completely out by the end of the month.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.88,0:11:45.34,Default-3,,0,0,0,,太倒霉了\N{\rEng}That sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.36,0:11:47.10,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是啊 是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah. Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.97,0:11:51.03,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是的 太倒霉了 真的太倒霉了\N{\rEng}Yeah, that sucks. It, it really sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.23,0:11:55.48,Default-3,,0,0,0,,互联网瘫痪 加州下沉\N{\rEng}The internet's down, and California's hanging by a thread.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.50,0:11:58.65,Default-3,,0,0,0,,还有大火 饥荒 疫情和各种灾难\N{\rEng}There's fires and famines and plagues and all the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.67,0:12:02.49,Default-3,,0,0,0,,连我们医院也快崩溃了\N{\rEng}I mean, it just the center doesn't hold.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.16,0:12:06.38,Default-3,,0,0,0,,没完没了\N{\rEng}It just won't let up.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.21,0:12:11.02,Default-3,,0,0,0,,那天还有多久？\N{\rEng}How long is this gonna go on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.73,0:12:14.41,Default-3,,0,0,0,,那之前还能撑多久？\N{\rEng}How much can we take before the whole thing...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.69,0:12:17.66,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我是说 天塌下来前\N{\rEng}before the whole thing goes apart, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.80,0:12:26.53,Default-3,,0,0,0,,{\rNote\fs12}卡尔·萨根是知名的美国天文学家{\r}\N我在教孩子们 {\u1}卡尔·萨根{\u0} 的理论\N{\rEng}I'm teaching the kids Carl Sagan right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.66,0:12:29.48,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你听说过他的宇宙历年法吗？\N{\rEng}You ever hear what he said about the cosmic calendar?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.75,0:12:33.08,Default-3,,0,0,0,,呃 想不起来 应该没听过\N{\rEng}Uh... I don't know. I don't think so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.10,0:12:36.34,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你知道 宇宙已有150亿年历史\N{\rEng}Well, the universe is 15 billion years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.36,0:12:41.24,Default-3,,0,0,0,,如果你把这150亿年\N{\rEng}And if you took all of that all, all 15 billion years
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.33,0:12:45.40,Default-3,,0,0,0,,都给它压缩到365天的日历中\N{\rEng}and compress them into a single calendar year,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.42,0:12:49.25,Default-3,,0,0,0,,那么宇宙大爆炸发生在1月1日第一秒\N{\rEng}then the Big Bang happens in the first second, January 1st.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.49,0:12:49.04,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(202,60)\fs28\1c00222222\b1\blur0.5}一    月    份
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.25,0:12:51.60,Default-3,,0,0,0,,而如今\N{\rEng}And, and today,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.60,0:12:58.82,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我们正处于12月31日 最后一天的最后一刻\N{\rEng}oh, right now, we're in the final millisecond of the last minute of the last day, December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.60,0:12:52.44,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(202,60)\fs28\1c00222222\b1\blur0.5}十 二 月 份
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.82,0:13:00.76,Default-3,,0,0,0,,回到起点\N{\rEng}But if you go back to the start,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.78,0:13:06.11,Default-3,,0,0,0,,回到大爆炸发生的1月1日夜里\N{\rEng}if the, if the Big Bang happens at midnight, January 1st,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.13,0:13:10.20,Default-3,,0,0,0,,日历里每个月等于12.5亿年\N{\rEng}then each month of this calendar is one and a quarter billion years long.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.22,0:13:12.48,Default-3,,0,0,0,,嘿 别考我数学\N{\rEng}Hey, nobody told me there was math on this exam.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.53,0:13:15.21,Default-3,,0,0,0,,宇宙在1月1日诞生\N{\rEng}The universe starts January 1st,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.23,0:13:19.90,Default-3,,0,0,0,,但此时我们的银河系还没形成 形成要到5月\N{\rEng}but the, uh, the Milky Way didn't form until May.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.23,0:13:19.54,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(138,146)\fs13\1c00222222\b1}五月份
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.93,0:13:25.44,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我们的太阳和地球 要到9月中旬才形成\N{\rEng}Our sun and our earth, they don't show up until mid-September.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.60,0:13:25.01,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(202,60)\fs28\1c00222222\b1\blur0.5}九   月   份
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.46,0:13:28.44,Default-3,,0,0,0,,生命不久后就有了 但没轮到我们\N{\rEng}Life appears soon after. But not us.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.46,0:13:31.57,Default-3,,0,0,0,,猜猜我们什么时候出现的？\N{\rEng}No. No, no, we don't appear for guess how long?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.59,0:13:33.79,Default-3,,0,0,0,,再说一遍 今天不考数学\N{\rEng}Again, I was told there'd be no math.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.81,0:13:36.08,Default-3,,0,0,0,,在12月31日\N{\rEng}December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.12,0:13:37.69,Default-3,,0,0,0,,出现在日历上的最后一天\N{\rEng}Last day on the calendar,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.30,0:13:37.75,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(202,60)\fs28\1c00222222\b1\blur0.5}十 二 月 份
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.77,0:13:44.31,Default-3,,0,0,0,,最早的人类出现在晚上10点半左右\N{\rEng}and the very first human beings on Earth made their debut around 10:30 p.m.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.35,0:13:47.81,Default-3,,0,0,0,,出现在最后一天的晚上10点半\N{\rEng}10:30 p.m. on the last day.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.83,0:13:52.20,Default-3,,0,0,0,,每一分钟代表着3万年\N{\rEng}And, um, every minute since then is 30,000 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.22,0:14:01.86,Default-3,,0,0,0,,晚上11:46 距离午夜14分钟 人类才学会用火\N{\rEng}So, 11:46 p.m., only 14 minutes ago, humanity tamed fire
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.88,0:14:05.79,Default-3,,0,0,0,,在距离午夜只剩几秒钟时\N{\rEng}and now we're out of minutes, we're into seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.93,0:14:07.83,Default-3,,0,0,0,,到11点59分20秒\N{\rEng}11:59 and 20 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.85,0:14:15.92,Default-3,,0,0,0,,动植物才被驯化 人类刚开始能制造工具\N{\rEng}the domestication of plants and animals begin, an application for the human talent for making tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.94,0:14:19.27,Default-3,,0,0,0,,到11点59分35秒\N{\rEng}11:59 and 35 seconds,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.29,0:14:25.06,Default-3,,0,0,0,,农耕社区演变为首批城市雏形\N{\rEng}agricultural communities evolved into the first cities.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.08,0:14:27.02,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我们记载的所有历史\N{\rEng}Our recorded history,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.04,0:14:29.76,Default-3,,0,0,0,,听说过的所有人\N{\rEng}everyone we've ever heard of,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.78,0:14:39.45,Default-3,,0,0,0,,所有历史书上的事 都只发生在最后10秒钟里\N{\rEng}every single thing in any one of our history books happens in the last 10 seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.49,0:14:47.41,Default-3,,0,0,0,,所有事都集中在最后一天最后一分钟的最后十秒\N{\rEng}The last 10 seconds of the last minute of the last day on the calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.41,0:14:50.62,Default-3,,0,0,0,,日历的最后一天\N{\rEng}December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.85,0:14:56.53,Default-3,,0,0,0,,该怎么回答你那天还有多久？\N{\rEng}So how long is it gonna go on?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.55,0:14:58.70,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我不知道 小菲\N{\rEng}I don't know, Fel.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.28,0:15:03.14,Default-3,,0,0,0,,要是你说得对 很可能真是这样\N{\rEng}If you're right, and you might be,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.16,0:15:07.02,Default-3,,0,0,0,,这可能就是末世 宇宙正在消亡\N{\rEng}that this really is the, the last times and the universe is dying,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.04,0:15:08.67,Default-3,,0,0,0,,就算它在快速消亡\N{\rEng}and let's just say it's a fast death,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.69,0:15:14.02,Default-3,,0,0,0,,即使这一切都发生在最后一秒\N{\rEng}even if all of this is happening in the, the last split second,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.04,0:15:15.98,Default-3,,0,0,0,,最后一微秒\N{\rEng}microsecond,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.00,0:15:18.25,Default-3,,0,0,0,,谁知道对我们来说是多久\N{\rEng}who knows how long that'll last.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.28,0:15:21.42,Default-3,,0,0,0,,也许是几秒钟 也可以是无限长\N{\rEng}Maybe seconds, maybe eons.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.44,0:15:27.86,Default-3,,0,0,0,,也许发生在宇宙吐出最后一口气的时候\N{\rEng}Maybe all this is happening as the cosmos burps out its last breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.88,0:15:36.55,Default-3,,0,0,0,,也许发生在宇宙最后一次心跳的时候\N{\rEng}Maybe it's all happening in the last single solitary heartbeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.11,0:15:40.94,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你真能说 马蒂\N{\rEng}Jesus, Marty.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.16,0:15:43.61,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是吧\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.73,0:15:52.79,Default-3,,0,0,0,,好了 小菲 我该挂了 我...\N{\rEng}Listen, Fel, I should go. I've, um...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.87,0:15:57.12,Default-3,,0,0,0,,还得批改试卷呢\N{\rEng}I've got tests to grade.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.65,0:15:59.34,Default-3,,0,0,0,,马蒂\N{\rEng}Marty...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.61,0:16:03.64,Default-3,,0,0,0,,一切都完了 我们也只剩下句真倒霉\N{\rEng}the world is going down the drain, and all we can say is, "That sucks."
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.66,0:16:07.58,Default-3,,0,0,0,,说不定谁都躲不掉这劫\N{\rEng}So, maybe we're going down the drain too.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.62,0:16:09.25,Default-3,,0,0,0,,说不定\N{\rEng}Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.45,0:16:11.73,Default-3,,0,0,0,,听说了吗 查克·克兰兹要退休了\N{\rEng}But, you know, Chuck Krantz is retiring.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.75,0:16:16.13,Default-3,,0,0,0,,都要天塌下来了 还有这个插曲\N{\rEng}So...I guess there's a gleam of light in the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.15,0:16:17.76,Default-3,,0,0,0,,听说了 39个非凡岁月\N{\rEng}Yes. Thirty-nine great years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.79,0:16:19.44,Default-3,,0,0,0,,哦 你也看到那个奇葩的广告牌了？\N{\rEng}Oh, you saw that weird billboard?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.46,0:16:21.44,Default-3,,0,0,0,,不 是从收音机里听到的广告\N{\rEng}No, it was an ad on the radio that, um,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.46,0:16:23.35,Default-3,,0,0,0,,之前跟你讲的那个国家电台\N{\rEng}that NPR show I was telling you about.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.37,0:16:26.68,Default-3,,0,0,0,,国资电台都开始打广告了 这真是世界末日了\N{\rEng}If they're running ads on NPR, it really is the end of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.70,0:16:30.62,Default-3,,0,0,0,,查克·克兰兹会怎么计算广告覆盖率\N{\rEng}Tell me, how does Chuck Krantz rate this kind of coverage?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.64,0:16:33.15,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我是说 他像个会计师\N{\rEng}I mean... looks like an accountant.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.17,0:16:35.25,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我从没听说过他\N{\rEng}I've never heard of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.39,0:16:37.20,Default-3,,0,0,0,,广告一定用了张老照片\N{\rEng}Used an old photo too, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.23,0:16:41.42,Default-3,,0,0,0,,他看着都不到40 咋来的40年工龄\N{\rEng}I mean, the guy barely looks 40 at all, let alone 40 years on the job.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.44,0:16:43.60,Default-3,,0,0,0,,无奇不有\N{\rEng}The world is full of mysteries.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.00,0:16:48.03,Default-3,,0,0,0,,嘿 马蒂 别喝烈酒了\N{\rEng}And, hey, no hard stuff, Marty.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.05,0:16:51.47,Default-3,,0,0,0,,喝点啤酒吧\N{\rEng}Okay? Have a beer instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.01,0:16:53.63,Default-3,,0,0,0,,遵命\N{\rEng}You got it.
