Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.44,0:25:59.19,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172,108)\frz30\fs9\b1\1c00AAAAAA}呼出失败 无信号
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.06,0:26:53.17,Note,,0,0,0,,{\move(180,30,200,60)\fs18\i1\frz5\1c&H665A31&\b1}查尔斯·查克·克兰兹
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.17,0:26:54.32,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(180,50)\fs18\i1\frz5\1c&H665A31&\b1}查尔斯·查克·克兰兹
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.17,0:26:54.32,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(190,260)\fs14\i1\frz8\1c&HA1BFB7&\b1}39个{\u1}非凡{\u0}岁月！
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.17,0:26:54.32,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(200,290)\fs14\i1\frz8\1c&HA1BFB7&\b1}谢谢你\N　查克！
Dialogue: 0,0:27:11.67,0:27:13.63,Default-3,,0,0,0,,还好吗 老先生？\N{\rEng}You okay, sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.72,0:27:17.00,Default-3,,0,0,0,,好 就歇歇脚\N{\rEng}Yeah. Just taking a rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.64,0:27:20.88,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我走去市中心看大地坑了\N{\rEng}I walked downtown to look at the sinkhole
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.90,0:27:22.93,Default-3,,0,0,0,,还用手机拍了几张照片\N{\rEng}and take a few pictures with my phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:22.95,0:27:26.28,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我以为电视台可能会想要\N{\rEng}Thought one of the local TV stations might be interested,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.30,0:27:30.54,Default-3,,0,0,0,,但全都停播了\N{\rEng}but they all seem to be off the air.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.56,0:27:33.67,Default-3,,0,0,0,,除了克兰兹的广告\N{\rEng}Except for pictures of Krantz.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.57,0:27:38.09,Default-3,,0,0,0,,到处都是克兰兹啊\N{\rEng}All Krantz all the time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.44,0:27:41.29,Default-3,,0,0,0,,-知道他是谁吗？ -不知道 \N{\rEng}-Any idea who he is? -None.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.31,0:27:46.65,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我问过至少二十多人 没人知道\N{\rEng}I've asked two dozen people, at least. Nobody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:46.67,0:27:51.13,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我们的克兰兹可是世界末日的领路人啊\N{\rEng}Our man, Krantz, is the Oz of the apocalypse.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.15,0:27:53.91,Default-3,,0,0,0,,最后的笑话\N{\rEng}Our last meme.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.93,0:27:56.31,Default-3,,0,0,0,,-你往哪走？ -丰收里 \N{\rEng}-Where are you heading? -Harvest Acres.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.33,0:27:59.61,Default-3,,0,0,0,,世外桃源般的小区\N{\rEng}Nice little enclave off the beaten track.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.63,0:28:02.04,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我正要去那儿\N{\rEng}I'm heading there myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.06,0:28:03.53,Default-3,,0,0,0,,-我前妻住那儿 -噢 \N{\rEng}-My ex lives there. -Huh.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.55,0:28:04.82,Default-3,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rEng}Well...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.90,0:28:07.25,Default-3,,0,0,0,,要一起去吗？\N{\rEng}I can walk with you if you like.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.27,0:28:09.54,Default-3,,0,0,0,,萨姆 你做什么工作的？\N{\rEng}What do you do, Sam?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.56,0:28:11.95,Default-3,,0,0,0,,如果还有工作的话\N{\rEng}If you still do anything, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.24,0:28:16.42,Default-3,,0,0,0,,亚伯勒殡仪馆的老板兼首席殡葬师\N{\rEng}Owner and chief undertaker for Yarborough Funeral Home.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.42,0:28:17.98,Default-3,,0,0,0,,噢 老天\N{\rEng}Oh, man!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.00,0:28:19.24,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.26,0:28:21.68,Default-3,,0,0,0,,生意之前好到爆\N{\rEng}We had a boom.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:21.70,0:28:22.99,Default-3,,0,0,0,,谈起这个就高兴\N{\rEng}It's hard to feel good about it,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.01,0:28:26.38,Default-3,,0,0,0,,最火的还是前几周\N{\rEng}but business was never better than it was a few weeks ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:27.14,0:28:32.78,Default-3,,0,0,0,,但我真正志向所在是气象学\N{\rEng}But my real interest's meteorology.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.80,0:28:36.21,Default-3,,0,0,0,,年轻时我曾想当电视上天气预报员\N{\rEng}Dreamed of being a television weatherman in my salad days,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.21,0:28:38.78,Default-3,,0,0,0,,也许能成全国台的\N{\rEng}maybe even one of the networks.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.80,0:28:41.05,Default-3,,0,0,0,,但 没成\N{\rEng}But n-no.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.07,0:28:42.96,Default-3,,0,0,0,,不过还继续关注着\N{\rEng}I keep up, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.98,0:28:45.53,Default-3,,0,0,0,,读有关的书\N{\rEng}Read the journals.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.55,0:28:52.10,Default-3,,0,0,0,,想听的话 有些我读到的奇闻异事\N{\rEng}And I can tell you something amazing if you want to hear.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.12,0:28:57.11,Default-3,,0,0,0,,大家都说一天有24小时 对吧？\N{\rEng}You know how people say there are 24 hours in a day?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.13,0:28:59.04,Default-3,,0,0,0,,其实他们错了\N{\rEng}Well, they're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.09,0:29:06.55,Default-3,,0,0,0,,在恒星日中一天有23小时零56分钟\N{\rEng}There were 23 hours and 56 minutes in a stellar day.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.41,0:29:15.88,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(250,126)\fs16\i1\frz5\1c&H665A31&\b1}查尔斯·查克·克兰兹
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.41,0:29:15.88,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(260,170)\fs11\i1\frz8\1c&HA4AC88&\b1}39个{\u1}非凡{\u0}岁月！
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.41,0:29:15.88,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,156)\fs11\i1\frz8\1c&HA4AC88&\b1}谢谢你\N　查克！
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.53,0:29:13.32,Default-3,,0,0,0,,还零几秒钟\N{\rEng}Plus a few odd seconds.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.53,0:29:15.02,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你说的是过去吧？\N{\rEng}There "were"?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.05,0:29:17.16,Default-3,,0,0,0,,根据我的计算...\N{\rEng}Based on my calculations,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.19,0:29:20.93,Default-3,,0,0,0,,相信我 我的数学很好\N{\rEng}which I assure you I can back up, my math is good,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.02,0:29:26.40,Default-3,,0,0,0,,现在一天有24小时零2分钟长\N{\rEng}there are now 24 hours and two minutes in a day.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:26.42,0:29:28.27,Default-3,,0,0,0,,知道这什么意思？\N{\rEng}Do you know what that means?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.29,0:29:30.44,Default-3,,0,0,0,,地球自转速度在减慢？\N{\rEng}Well, you're saying the Earth's rotation is slowing down?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.46,0:29:32.44,Default-3,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\rEng}Exactly.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.08,0:29:37.19,Default-3,,0,0,0,,很多人将这些灾难归咎于我们破坏环境\N{\rEng}Lot of folks think all of these disasters are 'cause of what we've done to the environment.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:37.21,0:29:38.95,Default-3,,0,0,0,,并非如此\N{\rEng}Not so.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.43,0:29:42.63,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我先承认 我们对待母亲非常坏\N{\rEng}I'm the first to admit, we treated our mother,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.65,0:29:46.42,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是的 地球母亲 万物之母\N{\rEng}yes, she's our mother, all of us, very badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.44,0:29:49.68,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我们肯定玷污了她 几近强暴\N{\rEng}Certainly molested her, if not outright raped her.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.70,0:29:56.86,Default-3,,0,0,0,,但比起宇宙那浩瀚机制 我们只不过是一粒尘埃\N{\rEng}But... we're puny compared to the great clock of the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.88,0:29:58.12,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是呀\N{\rEng}No.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.32,0:30:00.00,Default-3,,0,0,0,,不论是什么原因\N{\rEng}Whatever's happening
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.02,0:30:03.87,Default-3,,0,0,0,,问题绝对比环境恶化更大\N{\rEng}is much larger than environmental degradation.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.89,0:30:06.57,Default-3,,0,0,0,,这就是数学告诉我的\N{\rEng}The math says so.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.59,0:30:09.53,Default-3,,0,0,0,,数学能做很多事\N{\rEng}And, and math can do a lot of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.55,0:30:16.34,Default-3,,0,0,0,,数学可以是门艺术 但数学可不会撒谎\N{\rEng}I mean, math can be art... but it can't lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.77,0:30:20.80,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(122, 210)\fs10\fsp2\shad0.5\bord0.5\1c00AAAAAA}丰收里小区
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.82,0:30:25.24,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你看 我要先坐会儿\N{\rEng}You know what? I think I'll sit
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.26,0:30:32.94,Default-3,,0,0,0,,边欣赏日落 边歇歇脚\N{\rEng}and enjoy the sunset while I wait for the arthritis to settle a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.96,0:30:36.25,Default-3,,0,0,0,,要一起坐会儿吗？\N{\rEng}You care to join me?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.23,0:30:41.18,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我还想继续走\N{\rEng}I think I'll go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.49,0:30:44.82,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你前妻 我理解\N{\rEng}The ex. I understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:44.84,0:30:50.20,Default-3,,0,0,0,,好的 一路顺风 安德森先生\N{\rEng}Well, it was nice speaking with you, Mr. Anderson.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.37,0:31:31.72,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你好\N{\rEng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.19,0:31:33.68,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你好\N{\rEng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:34.07,0:31:39.18,Default-3,,0,0,0,,别怕 我正去我前妻那儿 菲莉西娅·安德森\N{\rEng}Don't worry. I'm going to see my ex-wife, Felicia Anderson.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.20,0:31:41.88,Default-3,,0,0,0,,她现在改回娘家姓戈登了\N{\rEng}I think she's back to Gordon now.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.90,0:31:44.97,Default-3,,0,0,0,,她住在费恩巷19号\N{\rEng}She lives on Fern Lane, number 19.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.99,0:31:48.42,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是的 我认识戈登小姐\N{\rEng}Yeah, I know Miss Gordon.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.86,0:31:51.23,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你大晚上出来干嘛？\N{\rEng}What are you doing out?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:51.61,0:31:54.95,Default-3,,0,0,0,,溜旱冰\N{\rEng}I wanted to go skating.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.83,0:31:58.64,Default-3,,0,0,0,,以前我特别喜欢溜旱冰\N{\rEng}I used to love skating.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.66,0:32:01.79,Default-3,,0,0,0,,那现在就该就去溜\N{\rEng}Then you should go skating.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.96,0:32:04.51,Default-3,,0,0,0,,也许我真该去溜\N{\rEng}Maybe I should.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:04.53,0:32:08.60,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你都跟戈登小姐分手了 咋还去见她？\N{\rEng}Why do you see Miss Gordon if she's your ex?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.62,0:32:10.56,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我还是喜欢她\N{\rEng}I still like her.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.58,0:32:13.06,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你们吵架吗？\N{\rEng}Do you fight?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.15,0:32:14.96,Default-3,,0,0,0,,以前吵\N{\rEng}We used to.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.94,0:32:18.05,Default-3,,0,0,0,,分手后 我们相处得更好了\N{\rEng}We get along better now that we're exes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.07,0:32:21.38,Default-3,,0,0,0,,戈登小姐有时会来送她烤的姜饼干\N{\rEng}Miss Gordon gives us gingersnap cookies sometimes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:21.41,0:32:23.20,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我其实更喜欢奥利奥 不过...\N{\rEng}I like Oreos better, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.22,0:32:27.07,Default-3,,0,0,0,,就像是盒巧克力 不能每颗都合心意 对吧？\N{\rEng}That's just the way the cookie crumbles, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.07,0:32:28.64,Default-3,,0,0,0,,姜饼干里没巧克力\N{\rEng}Gingersnaps don't crumble.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.64,0:32:30.85,Default-3,,0,0,0,,除非和奥利奥一起吃...\N{\rEng}At least not until you crunch them...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.22,0:32:42.54,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你抓紧回家吧\N{\rEng}You better go home, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.57,0:32:47.62,Default-3,,0,0,0,,没路灯 天太黑 没法溜\N{\rEng}It's too dark for skating without streetlights.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.92,0:32:52.23,Default-3,,0,0,0,,会没事吗？\N{\rEng}Is everything gonna be okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:54.89,0:32:56.88,Default-3,,0,0,0,,当然会\N{\rEng}Sure it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.58,0:33:08.13,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(110,110)\frz10\i1\blur0.5\1c&HCCDF97&}谢谢你\N　查克！
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.14,0:33:32.92,Default-3,,0,0,0,,回家去\N{\rEng}Go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.66,0:33:36.86,Default-3,,0,0,0,,回家去找你爸妈\N{\rEng}Go home to your Mom and Dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.15,0:33:40.56,Default-3,,0,0,0,,抓紧\N{\rEng}Do it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.41,0:34:22.45,Default-3,,0,0,0,,哦 谢天谢地 谢天谢地\N{\rEng}Oh, thank God. Oh, thank God.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.84,0:34:26.64,Default-3,,0,0,0,,-谢天谢地 -这些都 都... \N{\rEng}-Thank God. -They, they just...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.24,0:34:31.09,Default-3,,0,0,0,,这些都突然冒出来了\N{\rEng}They just, they just started showing up.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.11,0:34:33.81,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我知道 我知道 我也看到了\N{\rEng}No, I know, I know, I saw.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.90,0:34:35.97,Default-3,,0,0,0,,只是这个小区吗？\N{\rEng}Is it just here?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.99,0:34:38.44,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我觉得到处都有\N{\rEng}I think it's everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.90,0:34:43.33,Default-3,,0,0,0,,看起来时候到了\N{\rEng}I think it's almost...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.00,0:34:48.43,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是啊\N{\rEng}Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.17,0:34:51.86,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是的 时候到了\N{\rEng}Yeah, I think it's almost...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.28,0:36:35.78,Default-3,,0,0,0,,这是我见过的最亮的星空\N{\rEng}It's the brightest I've ever seen the stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:40.20,0:36:42.45,Default-3,,0,0,0,,看那里\N{\rEng}Just look at that.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.42,0:36:47.23,Default-3,,0,0,0,,那是天鹰座\N{\rEng}There's Aquila the eagle.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.25,0:36:48.68,Default-3,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rEng}Mm-hm.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.21,0:36:50.42,Default-3,,0,0,0,,那是...\N{\rEng}There's, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.86,0:36:53.95,Default-3,,0,0,0,,天鹅座\N{\rEng}Cygnus the swan.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.52,0:37:03.75,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你看到了吗？\N{\rEng}You see it?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.67,0:37:18.97,Default-3,,0,0,0,,那是北极...\N{\rEng}And there's the North Sta...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.33,0:37:24.70,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你看到刚才那个吗？\N{\rEng}Did you just see that?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.72,0:37:26.34,Default-3,,0,0,0,,看到了\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.42,0:37:33.72,Default-3,,0,0,0,,火星也没了\N{\rEng}There goes Mars.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.53,0:37:51.51,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我好怕\N{\rEng}I'm scared.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.45,0:37:55.34,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我也是\N{\rEng}I am too.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.36,0:37:57.92,Default-3,,0,0,0,,没事的 亲爱的\N{\rEng}It's okay, honey.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.10,0:38:01.88,Default-3,,0,0,0,,你先走一步\N{\rEng}You go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.93,0:38:07.61,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我们到那里再重逢\N{\rEng}You go on ahead, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.90,0:38:14.44,Default-3,,0,0,0,,活了才39年\N{\rEng}Just thirty-nine years.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.35,0:38:24.64,Default-3,,0,0,0,,是39个非凡岁月\N{\rEng}Thirty-nine great years.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.40,0:38:33.15,Default-3,,0,0,0,,谢谢你 查克\N{\rEng}Thanks, Chuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:58.07,0:38:59.42,Default-3,,0,0,0,,我爱...\N{\rEng}I love y...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.13,0:39:20.69,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(193,130)\fs14\fsp3\fad(300,300)}第二幕
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.50,0:39:20.69,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(193,172)\fs14\fsp3\fad(300,300)}街头艺人万岁
Dialogue: 0,0:39:23.71,0:39:27.41,Default-2,,0,0,0,,多亏她那开着旧面包车的朋友麦克帮忙\N{\rEng}With the help of her friend, Mac, who has an old van,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.50,0:39:30.82,Default-2,,0,0,0,,泰勒·弗兰克才能把架子鼓摆到\N{\rEng}Taylor Franck sets up her drum kit in
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.85,0:39:35.11,Default-2,,0,0,0,,第八街长廊上她最喜欢的那个地方\N{\rEng}her favored spot on the Eighth Street Promenade.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.11,0:39:39.18,Default-2,,0,0,0,,这天是周四下午\N{\rEng}It's Thursday afternoon.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.20,0:39:42.05,Default-2,,0,0,0,,这天的天气 真是绝了\N{\rEng}The weather is fucking gorgeous,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.08,0:39:46.10,Default-2,,0,0,0,,街上人来人往 大家都在幻想着周末\N{\rEng}and the streets are thronged with people looking forward to the weekend,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.12,0:39:49.06,Default-2,,0,0,0,,毕竟幻想总比现实好\N{\rEng}which is always better than the weekend itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.08,0:39:51.54,Default-2,,0,0,0,,-泰勒 都差不多了吧？ -嗯 谢了 \N{\rEng}-All good. Taylor? -Yeah, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:51.56,0:39:54.50,Default-2,,0,0,0,,老铁 别忘分我一成收入\N{\rEng}Ten percent is all the thanks I want, dude.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.61,0:40:00.95,Default-2,,0,0,0,,泰勒和麦克都在城堡街的心疗唱片店打零工\N{\rEng}Taylor, and Mac too, work part-time at Doctor Records on Castle Street.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.98,0:40:05.15,Default-2,,0,0,0,,打赏多时 泰勒挣得差不多跟打零工一样\N{\rEng}But on a good day Taylor can make almost as much busking.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.23,0:40:06.34,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(330,176)\shad0.5\bord0.5\1c&H586EAB&\fs20}魔 术 帽\N{\1c&H657D6D&\fs18}每笔打赏都会\N{\1c&H586EAB&\fs18\b1}精彩翻倍!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.32,0:40:12.81,Default-2,,0,0,0,,{\rNote\fs13}茱莉亚学院是世界顶尖的音乐学校{\r}\N当初考上 {\u1}茱莉亚{\u0} 时 她爸妈可没料到她会上街打鼓\N{\rEng}Busk-drumming isn't what her parents saw for her when she enrolled at Juilliard,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.89,0:40:16.02,Default-2,,0,0,0,,更不知道她现在还辍了学\N{\rEng}and they don't know yet that she dropped out.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:16.46,0:40:19.68,Default-2,,0,0,0,,在茱莉亚他们教你多动脑子\N{\rEng}Juilliard wanted you to think about what you were doing,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:19.77,0:40:29.94,Default-2,,0,0,0,,在泰勒眼里 跟着鼓点走就对了 多想一下灵感就跑了\N{\rEng}but as far as Taylor is concerned, the beat is your friend and thinking is the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.69,0:40:36.41,Default-2,,0,0,0,,她先热身 一开始节奏简单\N{\rEng}She starts warming up, going easy at first.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.43,0:40:39.20,Default-2,,0,0,0,,节奏缓慢 不敲牛铃\N{\rEng}slow tempo, no cowbell,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.40,0:40:44.60,Default-2,,0,0,0,,不在乎魔术帽空着 里面只有她自己放的钱\N{\rEng}not minding that the magic hat stays empty except for her two crumpled dollars
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.62,0:40:50.39,Default-2,,0,0,0,,还有个滑板小子随随便便丢进去的硬币\N{\rEng}and a quarter flipped contemptuously by a dude on a skateboard.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:50.41,0:40:54.21,Default-2,,0,0,0,,时间还早 总能找到切入点\N{\rEng}There is time. There is a way in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.23,0:41:00.52,Default-2,,0,0,0,,找到切入点才是占最大头的乐趣\N{\rEng}Finding the in is half the fun. Maybe even most of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:01.37,0:41:07.27,Default-2,,0,0,0,,珍妮丝·哈利迪在书店工作一天后正在回家\N{\rEng}Janice Halliday is on her way home from seven hours at Paper and Page,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.29,0:41:10.45,Default-2,,0,0,0,,大概会去海边走走\N{\rEng}and may walk all the way to the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.47,0:41:14.10,Default-2,,0,0,0,,谈了一年多的男友刚甩了她\N{\rEng}Her boyfriend of 16 months just broke up with her,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.12,0:41:16.57,Default-2,,0,0,0,,随便发个消息甩了她\N{\rEng}and he did it the modern way.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.17,0:41:16.70,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(274,108)\frz-12\fs9\1c00444444\b1}女：怎么不回我消息了？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.17,0:41:16.70,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(274,150)\frz-13\fs9\1c00444444\b1}男：咱俩不合适
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.17,0:41:16.70,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(274,174)\frz-13\fs9\1c00444444\b1}男：你是个好人
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.17,0:41:16.70,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(256,184)\frz-13\fs9\1c00444444\b1}男：继续做朋友？？
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.57,0:41:17.98,Default-2,,0,0,0,,王八蛋！\N{\rEng}Motherfucker!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:18.00,0:41:25.03,Default-2,,0,0,0,,这突如其来 犹如当头一棒把门关在脸上\N{\rEng}It was totally unexpected, like having a door slammed in your face just as you were getting ready to walk through it.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:25.05,0:41:26.59,Default-2,,0,0,0,,-那感觉... -真他妈离谱 \N{\rEng}-It was... -Fucking bullshit!
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.61,0:41:28.16,Default-2,,0,0,0,,...真他妈离谱\N{\rEng}...fucking bullshit.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.18,0:41:32.43,Default-2,,0,0,0,,她从没动过真情 也没天真地以为自己爱过他\N{\rEng}She isn't in love with him. never even kidded herself that she was.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.45,0:41:34.30,Default-2,,0,0,0,,-但依然... -他喵的糟透了 \N{\rEng}-But still it... -Fucking sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:34.32,0:41:37.61,Default-2,,0,0,0,,...打她个措手不及\N{\rEng}...is a dismaying shock just the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.63,0:41:42.65,Default-2,,0,0,0,,她打算回家后喝点酒 顺便哭一场\N{\rEng}She supposes she'll have some wine when she gets home and cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:42.67,0:41:48.09,Default-2,,0,0,0,,说不定还会播个爵士乐 在屋里醉舞一番\N{\rEng}Maybe queue up one of her big band playlists and dance drunk around the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.11,0:41:50.88,Default-2,,0,0,0,,她读高中时就爱跳舞\N{\rEng}She loved to dance in high school.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.90,0:41:53.80,Default-2,,0,0,0,,也许能借此重温当年那份快乐\N{\rEng}Maybe she can recapture a little of that happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:53.82,0:41:56.03,Default-2,,0,0,0,,-去你妈的 -你说什么？ \N{\rEng}-Fucking really?! -Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:56.05,0:41:58.52,Default-2,,0,0,0,,对不起 对不起 没说你 没说你\N{\rEng}Sorry, sorry, sorry. Not you, not you.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:59.34,0:42:00.96,Default-2,,0,0,0,,他喵的！\N{\rEng}Fuck!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.04,0:42:03.52,Default-2,,0,0,0,,查克的拿铁好了\N{\rEng}Got an oat milk latte for Chuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.46,0:42:04.65,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(192,130)\frz14\1c00222222\b1}查 克  {\fs20}^{\fs12}v{\fs20}^
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.48,0:42:06.32,Default-2,,0,0,0,,查尔斯·查克·克兰兹\N{\rEng}Charles Krantz,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:06.79,0:42:11.33,Default-2,,0,0,0,,在朋友眼中 他总一身会计行头\N{\rEng}Chuck to his friends, is dressed in the armor of accountancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:11.35,0:42:14.95,Default-2,,0,0,0,,灰西装 蓝衬衣配蓝领带\N{\rEng}Gray suit, blue shirt, blue tie.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.97,0:42:19.95,Default-2,,0,0,0,,脚上那双温莎牌皮鞋虽不贵 却耐穿\N{\rEng}His Samuel Windsor shoes are inexpensive but sturdy.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.97,0:42:26.22,Default-2,,0,0,0,,他来这参加个主题为“二十一世纪银行业”的研讨会\N{\rEng}He's here for a week-long conference titled "Banking in the 21st Century."
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.24,0:42:29.96,Default-2,,0,0,0,,他的中西部信托银行派他来的\N{\rEng}He's been sent by his bank, Midwest Trust,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.98,0:42:31.88,Default-2,,0,0,0,,全程报销\N{\rEng}all expenses paid.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.90,0:42:35.75,Default-2,,0,0,0,,查克对嘉宾和座谈都挺有兴趣\N{\rEng}Chuck has enjoyed the speakers and the panels.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.77,0:42:37.32,Default-2,,0,0,0,,他上过一个座谈会\N{\rEng}He was on one panel
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.34,0:42:42.37,Default-2,,0,0,0,,明天中午大会结束前还要再参加一个\N{\rEng}and is scheduled to be on another before the conference ends at noon tomorrow,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.39,0:42:48.76,Default-2,,0,0,0,,但他可不想下班后还和那群同行混在一起\N{\rEng}but has no wish to spend his off-duty hours in the company of 70 other accountants.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.78,0:42:54.12,Default-2,,0,0,0,,他精通会计的那套行话 也觉得自己能融入别的圈子\N{\rEng}He speaks their language, but likes to think he speaks others as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.14,0:42:59.94,Default-2,,0,0,0,,至少曾经那么自信 如今却大不如前了\N{\rEng}At least he did, although some of the vocabulary is now lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.96,0:43:06.00,Default-2,,0,0,0,,现在 他穿着他温莎牌牛津鞋正在午后散步\N{\rEng}Now, his sensible Samuel Windsor Oxfords are taking him for an afternoon walk.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:06.02,0:43:10.05,Default-2,,0,0,0,,现在的生活没能达到最初的设想\N{\rEng}His life is narrower than the one he once hoped for,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.07,0:43:12.41,Default-2,,0,0,0,,可他已经释然了\N{\rEng}but he's made peace with that.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.46,0:43:17.79,Default-2,,0,0,0,,他明白水往低处流是自然规律\N{\rEng}He understands that narrowing is the natural order of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:17.81,0:43:22.41,Default-2,,0,0,0,,他有个忠贞不渝的妻子叫珍妮\N{\rEng}He has a wife, Ginny,to whom he is scrupulously faithful,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:22.43,0:43:26.54,Default-2,,0,0,0,,还有个聪明风趣的儿子上初中\N{\rEng}and an intelligent, good-humored son in middle school.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.56,0:43:33.19,Default-2,,0,0,0,,他还有九个月可活 只不过他还不知道\N{\rEng}He also has only nine months to live, though he doesn't know that yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.61,0:43:43.94,Default-2,,0,0,0,,泰勒已经敲了十分钟了 分文未得 毫无灵感\N{\rEng}Taylor has been on the job for 10 minutes now and has nothing to show for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:44.97,0:43:48.91,Default-2,,0,0,0,,她看见个西装男朝她走来\N{\rEng}She sees a Mr. Businessman type coming toward her
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.93,0:43:51.43,Default-2,,0,0,0,,不知为何 他身上有股气息\N{\rEng}and something about him, God knows what,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.45,0:43:56.52,Default-2,,0,0,0,,让泰勒忍不住大张旗鼓宣布他登场了\N{\rEng}makes Taylor want to announce his approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.54,0:44:01.06,Default-2,,0,0,0,,她先用松弛的摇摆热场 又切换到更撩人的节奏\N{\rEng}She slips first into a reggae beat, then something slinkier.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.08,0:44:05.40,Default-2,,0,0,0,,今天头一次 泰勒火花被点燃\N{\rEng}And for the first time today, Taylor feels a spark
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.42,0:44:09.67,Default-2,,0,0,0,,便在核心鼓点上敲着牛铃\N{\rEng}and begins to whack the cowbell on the downbeat.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:09.69,0:44:11.10,Default-2,,0,0,0,,真带感\N{\rEng}It's pretty cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.12,0:44:17.92,Default-2,,0,0,0,,鼓点已经到来 那律动带你一路向前\N{\rEng}The groove has arrived, and the groove is like a road you want to follow.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:17.92,0:44:21.68,Default-2,,0,0,0,,她本可把节拍提快 玩点花样\N{\rEng}She could speed the beat up, get some tom in there,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.70,0:44:27.17,Default-2,,0,0,0,,但此刻目光是那西装男 多此一举反而不搭\N{\rEng}but she's watching Mr. Businessman and that seems wrong for this dude.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.19,0:44:33.69,Default-2,,0,0,0,,她以为那西装男只是路过 要去商务酒店\N{\rEng}She believes Mr. Businessman will just go on past on his way to the business hotel,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:33.71,0:44:38.87,Default-2,,0,0,0,,等他一走 泰勒再换节拍\N{\rEng}and when he's gone, Taylor will switch to something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.89,0:44:43.03,Default-2,,0,0,0,,可他却停下脚步\N{\rEng}But instead of floating on by...
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.95,0:47:02.10,Default-2,,0,0,0,,赏个脸\N{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:03.47,0:47:05.02,Default-2,,0,0,0,,来吧 小老妹\N{\rEng}Come on, little sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:05.61,0:47:06.72,Default-2,,0,0,0,,跳个舞吧\N{\rEng}Let's dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.74,0:47:08.26,Default-2,,0,0,0,,跳\N{\rEng}Dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:11.61,0:47:13.44,Default-2,,0,0,0,,对了\N{\rEng}Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.53,0:47:16.06,Default-2,,0,0,0,,我带你跳 有我别怕\N{\rEng}I'll lead you. I got you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:04.49,0:48:05.88,Default-2,,0,0,0,,啊\N{\rEng}Uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.63,0:48:14.25,Default-2,,0,0,0,,没事 眼镜的事儿 眼镜的事儿\N{\rEng}It's okay. It's my glasses. It's my glasses.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:54.86,0:49:55.99,Default-2,,0,0,0,,现在该做什么？\N{\rEng}What are we doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.78,0:49:57.82,Default-2,,0,0,0,,我也不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:14.71,0:50:16.69,Default-2,,0,0,0,,大伙 今天就到这了\N{\rEng}No more today, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:16.88,0:50:18.48,Default-2,,0,0,0,,今天就到这了\N{\rEng}No more today.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.84,0:50:22.25,Default-2,,0,0,0,,今天就到这了 得见好就收\N{\rEng}No more today. We gotta quit while we're ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.91,0:50:26.82,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(330,146)\shad0.5\bord0.5\1c&H586EAB&\fs20}魔 术 帽\N{\1c&H657D6D&\fs18}每笔打赏都会\N{\1c&H586EAB&\fs18\b1}精彩翻倍!
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.54,0:50:26.29,Default-2,,0,0,0,,要搭把手吗\N{\rEng}Do you need a-any help at all or...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.37,0:50:27.81,Default-2,,0,0,0,,好 帮把这个收起来\N{\rEng}Here, can you, uh, take this?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.89,0:50:29.42,Default-2,,0,0,0,,-好 -拧这里 \N{\rEng}-Sure. -Just, just spin the thingy here.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.50,0:50:31.47,Default-2,,0,0,0,,-小心别夹手了 -会雨过天晴的\N{\rEng}But watch out for your fingers. -It'll, it'll, it'll get 'em good.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.55,0:50:33.30,Default-2,,0,0,0,,懂了吧\N{\rEng}you know what I mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.37,0:50:35.50,Default-2,,0,0,0,,-好 好 -找点事散散心 \N{\rEng}-Yeah, yeah. -To doing something else.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:35.60,0:50:37.69,Default-2,,0,0,0,,刚太神奇了\N{\rEng}What just happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.77,0:50:39.69,Default-2,,0,0,0,,跳的太神了\N{\rEng}That was incredible.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.78,0:50:41.13,Default-2,,0,0,0,,你们是舞蹈演员吗？\N{\rEng}You dance for a living?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:41.21,0:50:42.87,Default-2,,0,0,0,,哦 不 不\N{\rEng}No. Oh, no. I...
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.95,0:50:44.87,Default-2,,0,0,0,,-不 不是的 -你做什么的？ \N{\rEng}-No, I do not, sir. -What do you do for a living?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:44.96,0:50:46.85,Default-2,,0,0,0,,哎呦 我好像不小心搞坏了\N{\rEng}Oh, no, I think I... Did I... I didn't break it, did I?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:46.87,0:50:49.07,Default-2,,0,0,0,,这个好像坏了\N{\rEng}I think he broke it.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:50.31,0:50:51.84,Default-2,,0,0,0,,去喷泉吧\N{\rEng}Let's hit the pond.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.92,0:50:54.17,Default-2,,0,0,0,,那儿没停车位\N{\rEng}We'll never find parking by the Common.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:54.53,0:50:55.57,Default-2,,0,0,0,,那也要停\N{\rEng}We will today.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.92,0:51:01.19,Default-2,,0,0,0,,今天 就像魔术一样\N{\rEng}Today...is magic.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.67,0:51:09.47,Default-2,,0,0,0,,你们在哪练的这身舞功？\N{\rEng}Where did you learn to dance like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:15.16,0:51:17.40,Default-2,,0,0,0,,别 别 别 那是你赚的\N{\rEng}Oh, no, no, no, that's yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.42,0:51:19.01,Default-2,,0,0,0,,不 有福同享\N{\rEng}Nope, we split it even.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:19.03,0:51:23.47,Default-2,,0,0,0,,要我自己敲 一天也赚不了这么多\N{\rEng}By myself, I wouldn't have made half as much if I drummed till midnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.44,0:51:33.61,Default-2,,0,0,0,,你没事吧？\N{\rEng}You okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.66,0:51:37.34,Default-2,,0,0,0,,还好\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:38.92,0:51:41.69,Default-2,,0,0,0,,就是有点头疼\N{\rEng}Yeah. Just one of my headaches.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.36,0:51:45.82,Default-2,,0,0,0,,不了 不了 真用不着 你留着吧\N{\rEng}Oh, no, no, no. Come on. I don't need it. You keep it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.84,0:51:48.26,Default-2,,0,0,0,,来吧 老兄 你应得的\N{\rEng}Come on, man, you earned it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.28,0:51:55.00,Default-2,,0,0,0,,拿去吃顿饭 转手送人也行 但这钱我偏要交给你\N{\rEng}Buy yourself dinner. Give it away. But I'm handing it to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.64,0:51:59.40,Default-2,,0,0,0,,你们干这行都能当职业了\N{\rEng}You could do this for a living, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.42,0:52:01.36,Default-2,,0,0,0,,我可不敢这么说\N{\rEng}I don't know about that.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.38,0:52:05.30,Default-2,,0,0,0,,我真觉得靠街头表演 我们能红 能赚大钱\N{\rEng}I really think we could busk our way to fame and fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.78,0:52:11.83,Default-2,,0,0,0,,你怎么会停在我面前？\N{\rEng}What made you stop in front of me?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.04,0:52:16.62,Default-2,,0,0,0,,又为什么突然跳起舞？\N{\rEng}Why did you start moving?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.90,0:52:23.47,Default-2,,0,0,0,,他本可以说 鼓点让他想起了他那不成气候的追旧青年乐队\N{\rEng}He could say it was because he was thinking about his old half-assed band, The Retros,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.49,0:52:29.37,Default-2,,0,0,0,,还有他多么的喜欢跟着节奏跳舞\N{\rEng}and how he liked to dance across the stage during instrumental breaks.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:29.41,0:52:31.16,Default-2,,0,0,0,,但他没这么说\N{\rEng}But that's not it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:34.59,0:52:36.76,Default-2,,0,0,0,,我也说不清\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.50,0:52:40.96,Default-2,,0,0,0,,泰勒 该走了\N{\rEng}Taylor, we gotta roll,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.98,0:52:44.45,Default-2,,0,0,0,,不然你赚的钱都得交罚单了\N{\rEng}or you're gonna end up spending your take on my parking ticket.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:44.99,0:52:48.06,Default-2,,0,0,0,,你们不考虑转行跳舞吗？\N{\rEng}So, you guys don't want a career change?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.08,0:52:49.97,Default-2,,0,0,0,,转行？\N{\rEng}Career change? How... I mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.99,0:52:52.28,Default-2,,0,0,0,,我们肯定能闯出名堂\N{\rEng}We'll make a name for ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.39,0:52:55.98,Default-2,,0,0,0,,别急着走 先进来一下\N{\rEng}You got to get in here before you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.00,0:52:58.07,Default-2,,0,0,0,,-来个大团抱！ -哦 哦 好 \N{\rEng}-Group hug. -Oh, oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:58.09,0:52:59.40,Default-2,,0,0,0,,-大团抱！ -来 \N{\rEng}-Group hug. -Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.48,0:53:00.98,Default-2,,0,0,0,,快 快 快\N{\rEng}Go.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:01.00,0:53:02.60,Default-2,,0,0,0,,来 来\N{\rEng}Come on.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:08.88,0:53:10.86,Default-2,,0,0,0,,街头艺人万岁\N{\rEng}Buskers forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.88,0:53:12.43,Default-2,,0,0,0,,好了 好了\N{\rEng}Yeah. Buskers forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.45,0:53:15.69,Default-2,,0,0,0,,得赶在贴罚单前抓紧走\N{\rEng}We gotta roll before the meter maid shows up.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.94,0:53:22.61,Default-2,,0,0,0,,真替你难过\N{\rEng}I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.07,0:53:24.31,Default-2,,0,0,0,,真倒霉\N{\rEng}That sucks.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.33,0:53:26.29,Default-2,,0,0,0,,这确实倒霉\N{\rEng}It does suck.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.94,0:53:28.88,Default-2,,0,0,0,,我真觉得他人还不错\N{\rEng}I thought he was a nice guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.90,0:53:32.42,Default-2,,0,0,0,,床上功夫也到位 我们在一起挺开心的\N{\rEng}He was a pretty good lover, and we had fun and all that.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:32.69,0:53:37.37,Default-2,,0,0,0,,我回去得找下我们跳舞的视频 估计会上热搜\N{\rEng}If I can find a video of us dancing, which I'm gonna look because I bet we go viral,
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.39,0:53:44.94,Default-2,,0,0,0,,然后转发给他 再附句“这就是你错过的缘分”\N{\rEng}I'm gonna send it to him with a text, a text that says, "This is what you're missing."
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.58,0:53:53.68,Default-2,,0,0,0,,你会没事的\N{\rEng}You're gonna be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:55.06,0:53:58.71,Default-2,,0,0,0,,我不是全都懂 可这件事我很清楚\N{\rEng}I don't know a lot, but I know that much.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.41,0:54:07.64,Default-2,,0,0,0,,光辉就在你前面 往前迈一步乌云就消散\N{\rEng}You got a bright sunbeam in front of you, and you're gonna step right into it, I can tell.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:08.07,0:54:09.24,Default-2,,0,0,0,,但现在\N{\rEng}But yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.38,0:54:14.35,Default-2,,0,0,0,,真倒霉 没啥好说的\N{\rEng}It sucks. Not much else to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.64,0:54:21.02,Default-2,,0,0,0,,一切都完了 我们也只剩下句真倒霉\N{\rEng}Everything goes down the drain, and all we can say is, "That sucks."
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.05,0:54:22.22,Default-2,,0,0,0,,对\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.04,0:54:26.94,Default-2,,0,0,0,,说不定谁都躲不掉这劫\N{\rEng}Maybe we're going down the drain too.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.96,0:54:28.64,Default-2,,0,0,0,,说不定\N{\rEng}Maybe.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.66,0:54:32.42,Default-2,,0,0,0,,我走这条路\N{\rEng}I'm this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:34.58,0:54:37.39,Default-2,,0,0,0,,我往那边走\N{\rEng}Uh, I'm that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.24,0:54:44.62,Default-2,,0,0,0,,多谢你陪我跳舞\N{\rEng}Thank you for the dance.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.03,0:55:42.36,Default-2,,0,0,0,,当他走过泰勒摆鼓的地方\N{\rEng}As he passes the place where Taylor set up her drums,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.38,0:55:46.43,Default-2,,0,0,0,,那两个问题又冒了出来\N{\rEng}those two questions recur.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.30,0:55:51.28,Default-2,,0,0,0,,为什么要停下脚步听？\N{\rEng}Why did he stop to listen?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:51.30,0:55:56.27,Default-2,,0,0,0,,又为什么要跳起舞？\N{\rEng}And why did he start to dance?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:57.05,0:56:00.13,Default-2,,0,0,0,,他自己也想不通\N{\rEng}He doesn't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:00.31,0:56:06.21,Default-2,,0,0,0,,就算真有答案能够让这段回忆更动人吗？\N{\rEng}And would answers make a good thing better?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.23,0:56:09.91,Default-2,,0,0,0,,后来 他走路都成问题\N{\rEng}Later, he'll lose the ability to walk,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.93,0:56:14.74,Default-2,,0,0,0,,和那个小老妹跳舞成了个传说\N{\rEng}never mind dancing with little sister on the promenade.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.76,0:56:19.14,Default-2,,0,0,0,,再后来 他咀嚼都成了难题\N{\rEng}Later, he'll lose the ability to chew food.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.16,0:56:23.19,Default-2,,0,0,0,,再后来 他记不住妻子的名字\N{\rEng}Later, he'll forget his wife's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.21,0:56:29.15,Default-2,,0,0,0,,到最后 他分不清白日黑夜\N{\rEng}Later, he'll lose his grip on the difference between waking and sleeping
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.17,0:56:38.16,Default-2,,0,0,0,,陷入一种让人质疑生命意义的巨大痛苦中\N{\rEng}and enter a land of pain so great he will wonder why God made the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.18,0:56:45.08,Default-2,,0,0,0,,但有时 他还会记得当初把公文包一丢\N{\rEng}What he will remember, occasionally, is how he stopped and dropped his briefcase
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.10,0:56:49.69,Default-2,,0,0,0,,跟着鼓点起舞的感觉\N{\rEng}and began to move his hips to the beat of the drums.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.71,0:56:55.83,Default-2,,0,0,0,,他会觉得 这就是上帝让世界存在的意义\N{\rEng}And he will think that is why God made the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:55.85,0:56:57.93,Default-2,,0,0,0,,仅此而已\N{\rEng}Just that.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.08,0:57:19.16,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(193,130)\fs14\fsp3\fad(300,300)}第一幕
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.39,0:57:19.16,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(193,172)\fs14\fsp3\fad(300,300)}我包罗万象
Dialogue: 0,0:57:21.05,0:57:24.94,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克一直盼着能有个小妹妹\N{\rEng}Chuck was looking forward to having a baby sister.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.96,0:57:28.95,Default-1,,0,0,0,,更盼着父母能赶紧回来\N{\rEng}Of course, he was also looking forward to having parents,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.97,0:57:37.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,谁料95号高架上结的冰让一切化为泡影\N{\rEng}but none of that worked out thanks to a patch 95 of well-hidden ice on an I-95 overpass.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:38.59,0:57:41.13,Default-1,,0,0,0,,事发时查克没在车上\N{\rEng}Chuck wasn't in the car when it happened
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.15,0:57:43.92,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他父母去享受二人世界\N{\rEng}because his parents were having a dinner date
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.94,0:57:47.36,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那天晚上他爷爷奶奶带他\N{\rEng}and he was being babysat by his grandparents,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.38,0:57:51.27,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他那会儿还叫他们阿爷阿奶\N{\rEng}who, at the time, he was still calling Zaydee and Bubbie.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.29,0:57:52.84,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他那时七岁了\N{\rEng}He was seven years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.86,0:57:54.92,Default-1,,0,0,0,,真赞喔\N{\rEng}Excellent job.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.21,0:58:01.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,一年半载 屋子里全是悲伤\N{\rEng}For a year and a half, it was a house of unadulterated sadness.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:01.09,0:58:05.99,Default-1,,0,0,0,,对阿尔比和莎拉·克兰兹来说 不只是儿子和儿媳没了\N{\rEng}Albie and Sarah Krantz had not only lost their son and daughter-in-law...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:06.01,0:58:07.47,Default-1,,0,0,0,,咋不吃饭了？\N{\rEng}Why're you not eating?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.49,0:58:12.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那本该三个月后出生的孙女也没了\N{\rEng}...they had lost the granddaughter who would've been born just three months later.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.09,0:58:13.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,咋回事儿？\N{\rEng}What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.79,0:58:16.08,Default-1,,0,0,0,,名字都选好了...\N{\rEng}The name had already been picked out...
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.10,0:58:18.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-她叫艾雨莎 -艾雨莎 \N{\rEng}-Her name is Alyssa. -...Alyssa.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.54,0:58:22.06,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克说那名字听着像下雨时\N{\rEng}When Chuck said that sounded to him like rain,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.06,0:58:26.13,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他妈哭笑不得\N{\rEng}his mother had laughed and cried at the same time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:26.15,0:58:29.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他永远忘不了那表情\N{\rEng}He never forgot that.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.85,0:58:34.80,Default-1,,0,0,0,,阿尔比靠两件事来排解悲伤\N{\rEng}Albie processed his grief by turning to his two absolutes,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.82,0:58:38.19,Default-1,,0,0,0,,算账和喝酒\N{\rEng}numbers and alcohol.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.21,0:58:43.11,Default-1,,0,0,0,,但对莎拉来说 一切却都失去了滋味\N{\rEng}Sarah, though, could find no joy in her usual pleasures.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:43.13,0:58:47.98,Default-1,,0,0,0,,曾让她陶醉的音乐 艺术和美食\N{\rEng}She loved the flavors of life, music, art, and food,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:48.00,0:58:53.50,Default-1,,0,0,0,,如今都索然无味\N{\rEng}but now, found the world quiet and gray and flavorless.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:55.36,0:58:59.86,Default-1,,0,0,0,,随着时间流逝 家里又慢慢有了些温暖\N{\rEng}Some of the good feelings came back into the house with time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.88,0:59:03.48,Default-1,,0,0,0,,事故后全靠外卖度日\N{\rEng}There were a lot of takeout meals after the accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:03.50,0:59:08.74,Default-1,,0,0,0,,但查克快十岁那年 他奶奶又重新下厨\N{\rEng}but around the time Chuck turned 10, his grandma started cooking again.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.76,0:59:12.59,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她做饭时爱放摇滚乐\N{\rEng}She liked rock-and-roll while she was cooking.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.61,0:59:20.60,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克肯定觉得太潮了 可她显然乐在其中\N{\rEng}Music Chuck would've thought much too young for her, but which she clearly enjoyed.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.23,0:59:42.44,Default-1,,0,0,0,,来吧 小老弟 来跳舞吧\N{\rEng}Come on, little brother, let's dance.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.58,1:00:13.79,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172,138)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5}《西区故事》
Dialogue: 0,1:00:16.24,1:00:17.11,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172,138)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5}《雨中曲》
Dialogue: 0,1:00:18.60,1:00:19.73,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172,138)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5}《歌厅》
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.84,1:00:23.98,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172,138)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5}《爵士春秋》
Dialogue: 0,1:00:28.39,1:00:30.23,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(172,138)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5}《封面女郎》
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.21,1:00:37.51,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(340,16)\fs13\shad0.5\bord0.5}电影《封面女郎》(1944)
Dialogue: 0,1:00:37.54,1:00:42.38,Default-1,,0,0,0,,小宝 你有本事学会 你天生是跳舞的料\N{\rEng}You could learn those moves, kiddo. You're a natural.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.40,1:00:43.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你在哪学的？\N{\rEng}Wh-Where did you learn?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:43.81,1:00:45.64,Default-1,,0,0,0,,高中\N{\rEng}High school.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:46.07,1:00:49.32,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你上高中的时候是什么样的？\N{\rEng}What were you like in high school?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.34,1:00:51.67,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我可是个小辣妹\N{\rEng}I was a kusit.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:51.69,1:00:54.21,Default-1,,0,0,0,,千万别把我这话告诉你阿爷哦\N{\rEng}But don't you tell your Zaydee I said that.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.24,1:00:57.09,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他是个老古董\N{\rEng}He's old school, that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:58.57,1:01:01.32,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克守口如瓶\N{\rEng}Chuck never told.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.58,1:01:05.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他把爷爷奶奶家处处都当自己家\N{\rEng}His grandparents' house became every inch his home
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.89,1:01:11.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,除了塔尖阁楼\N{\rEng}with one exception. the cupola on the roof.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.89,1:01:16.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克被严令禁止进那阁楼\N{\rEng}Chuck was forbidden to go into the cupola.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.93,1:01:23.36,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那是他爷爷的一条铁律 不容置疑\N{\rEng}That was his grandfather's rule, and it was absolute, emphatic.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:23.38,1:01:26.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他爷爷阿尔比做事宽容\N{\rEng}Albie wasn't a stern man in other matters.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.77,1:01:30.06,Default-1,,0,0,0,,平时人挺温和的\N{\rEng}He was downright gentle in most respects.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.08,1:01:34.54,Default-1,,0,0,0,,偏偏在这事上绝不讲情面\N{\rEng}But on this point, he was rigid.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:35.29,1:01:39.23,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克可不止问过一次\N{\rEng}Chuck asked about it, of course, and more than once.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:39.26,1:01:43.24,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那上头有什么？从高高的窗户能看到啥？\N{\rEng}What was up there? What could you see from the high window?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:43.26,1:01:48.31,Default-1,,0,0,0,,最重要的是 为啥老是锁着？\N{\rEng}And the big question, why was the room locked?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:48.49,1:01:49.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他奶奶说...\N{\rEng}Grandma said...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.37,1:01:51.88,Default-1,,0,0,0,,楼上地板不结实 一踩就会坍下去\N{\rEng}Because the floor isn't safe and you might go right through it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:51.91,1:01:52.82,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他爷爷说...\N{\rEng}Grandpa said...
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.82,1:01:56.08,Default-1,,0,0,0,,由于那烂地板 屋子里空无一物\N{\rEng}There's nothing up there because of that rotten floor.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.08,1:01:59.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你往窗外瞅 也就只能看到商场\N{\rEng}And the only thing you can see through the windows is the shopping center.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:59.98,1:02:05.39,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他一直这么说 直到查克十一岁生日前一晚\N{\rEng}He said that until, one night, just before Chuck's 11th birthday,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.42,1:02:08.10,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他才吐出部分实情\N{\rEng}when he told at least part of the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:08.10,1:02:09.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}宇宙历年法\N{\rEng}{\i1}The cosmic calendar
Dialogue: 0,1:02:09.81,1:02:14.54,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}把宇宙的历史压缩到一本365天日历\N{\rEng}{\i1}compresses the local history of the universe into a single year.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.56,1:02:17.10,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}从1月1日宇宙诞生算起\N{\rEng}{\i1}If the universe began on January 1st,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.12,1:02:19.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}我们的银河系要到5月才出现\N{\rEng}{\i1}it was not until May that the Milky Way formed.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.87,1:02:22.72,Default-1,,0,0,0,,俗话说酒后吐真言\N{\rEng}Drinking is not good for secrets.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.74,1:02:28.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,当儿子 儿媳还有那个名字听着像下雨的\N{\rEng}And after the death of his son, daughter-in-law, and granddaughter-to-be,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.18,1:02:30.88,Default-1,,0,0,0,,未来孙女艾雨莎全都去世后\N{\rEng}Alyssa, who sounds like rain,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.90,1:02:33.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,阿尔比·克兰兹就拼命喝酒\N{\rEng}Albie Krantz drank a great deal.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.73,1:02:37.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}人类全部的历史 都在\N{\rEng}{\i1}Everything humans have ever done occurred in that bright speck
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.45,1:02:41.00,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}这本日历的最后一天\N{\rEng}{\i1}at the lower right of the cosmic calendar.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.00,1:02:46.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我打赌 从阁楼往外看 能看到西福商场\N{\rEng}I'll bet you could see way past the Westford Mall from the cupola.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.98,1:02:52.36,Default-1,,0,0,0,,整座小镇肯定也能看得一清二楚\N{\rEng}You gotta be able to see the whole town from up there, I bet.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.38,1:02:58.71,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要真上去了 你看见的可不只是风景\N{\rEng}If you went up there, you might see a lot more than you wanted.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.73,1:03:01.20,Default-1,,0,0,0,,小查 这门紧锁是有原因的\N{\rEng}That's why it's locked, Chucko.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:01.20,1:03:04.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}日历里每个月代表12.5亿年\N{\rEng}{\i1}Every month is one and a quarter billion years long.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.39,1:03:07.20,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}每一天代表4000万年\N{\rEng}{\i1}Each day represents 40 million years.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.20,1:03:10.21,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他想问清楚\N{\rEng}He wanted to ask what Grandpa meant.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.35,1:03:14.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,尽管他才10岁\N{\rEng}But the adult part of him, not there in person, no, not at 10,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.18,1:03:19.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,可脑子里的成熟声音冒出来\N{\rEng}but something that had begun to speak on rare occasions,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.09,1:03:26.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,告诉他别吭声 安静地等着\N{\rEng}told him to be quiet. Be quiet and wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.16,1:03:31.22,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}人类的全部历史就像我手掌那么大\N{\rEng}{\i1}But all of human history would occupy an area the size of my hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.24,1:03:36.29,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}现在让我们回到太古时代...\N{\rEng}{\i1}We're just beginning to trace the long and tortuous path which began with the primeval...
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.38,1:03:39.49,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你知道这房子是什么风格的吗？\N{\rEng}You know what style of house this is?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:39.51,1:03:41.01,Default-1,,0,0,0,,维多利亚风格\N{\rEng}Victorian.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.03,1:03:42.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,没错\N{\rEng}That's right.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:43.34,1:03:49.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,可不是仿古的 1885年建的正经维多利亚式\N{\rEng}And not pretend Victorian either. It was built in 1885.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:49.39,1:03:52.42,Default-1,,0,0,0,,后来翻新过大概六次吧\N{\rEng}It's been remodeled half a dozen times since.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.44,1:03:57.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,可那阁楼一直保留至今\N{\rEng}But that cupola was there from the start.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.36,1:03:59.86,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我七十年代初搬来\N{\rEng}Been here since '71.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.88,1:04:05.31,Default-1,,0,0,0,,搬来至今 我上那阁楼都没到六次\N{\rEng}And in all those years, I haven't been up to that damn cupola half a dozen times.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:05.33,1:04:07.95,Default-1,,0,0,0,,因为地板烂了？\N{\rEng}'Cause the floor is rotted?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.76,1:04:11.82,Default-1,,0,0,0,,因为闹鬼\N{\rEng}'Cause it's full of ghosts.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:12.24,1:04:15.49,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}...发生在12月31日的晚上10点30分\N{\rEng}{\i1}...around 10:30 p.m. on December 31st.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:15.94,1:04:18.27,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-还记得圣诞述异那个故事吗？ -嗯 \N{\rEng}-Y-You remember Scrooge? -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.29,1:04:19.95,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那部叫做《圣诞欢歌》的电影？\N{\rEng}That Scrooge movie we watched?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.97,1:04:21.27,Default-1,,0,0,0,,记得\N{\rEng}I remember.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.29,1:04:24.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你觉得那算鬼故事吗？\N{\rEng}Do you think of that as a ghost story?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.95,1:04:26.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,应该算吧\N{\rEng}I-I-I guess so.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.65,1:04:30.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,有人说那是鬼故事\N{\rEng}Heard someone say it was a ghost story.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.87,1:04:34.74,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他吓的说“圣诞节未卜先知”\N{\rEng}Christmas Yet to Come.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.74,1:04:39.62,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}晚上11点59分20秒...\N{\rEng}{\i1}11:59:20，evening, last day of the...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:39.70,1:04:43.86,Default-1,,0,0,0,,杰弗里家那男孩一个月后就没了\N{\rEng}Jefferies boy was a month later.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:43.88,1:04:54.74,Default-1,,0,0,0,,亨利·彼得森拖得久些 等了四五年\N{\rEng}Henry Peterson, that took longer. Four...maybe five years on.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.76,1:05:02.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,到那时 阁楼里看到的 我几乎忘得精光\N{\rEng}And by then...I almost forgot what I saw up there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:02.55,1:05:05.40,Default-1,,0,0,0,,几乎\N{\rEng}Almost.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:06.93,1:05:11.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我说过再也不上去\N{\rEng}Said I'd never go back up there after that.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.65,1:05:18.12,Default-1,,0,0,0,,真不想上去 要不是为了莎拉\N{\rEng}And I wish I hadn't because of Sarah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.52,1:05:23.51,Default-1,,0,0,0,,为了你的阿奶 小查\N{\rEng}Because of your Bubbie, Chucky.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.53,1:05:27.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,最疼你的阿奶\N{\rEng}Your sweet Bubbie.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:27.45,1:05:30.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,都是面包\N{\rEng}And the bread.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.36,1:05:34.94,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}我们听说过的所有人...\N{\rEng}{\i1}Every person we've ever heard of, somewhere in there...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.02,1:05:38.88,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这就是等待 小查\N{\rEng}It's the waiting, Chucko.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:39.11,1:05:41.20,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这是最难熬的\N{\rEng}That's the hard part.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:41.20,1:05:43.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}所有历史书上的事 都只...\N{\rEng}{\i1}Everything in the history books happended...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.00,1:05:49.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}发生在这本日历最后10秒钟里\N{\rEng}{\i1}here in the last 10 seconds of the cosmic calendar.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.18,1:05:52.51,Default-1,,0,0,0,,呜 外面真冷\N{\rEng}Ooh! It's getting cold out there.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.53,1:05:56.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,维拉向大家问好 还感谢我煲的汤\N{\rEng}Vera says hi. She says thanks for the soup.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.18,1:05:59.28,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她把八卦全抖给我 抖得可带劲了\N{\rEng}She laid the gossip on me, laid it good.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.30,1:06:02.35,Default-1,,0,0,0,,当然 要不然咱咋离不开她呢\N{\rEng}Of course...That's why we have a Vera, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.37,1:06:04.38,Default-1,,0,0,0,,有什么新鲜事吗？\N{\rEng}So, what's the latest?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.40,1:06:09.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不知道你听说了没 凯伦和马蒂在搞婚姻咨询\N{\rEng}Well, I don't know if you've heard, but Trish is saying Karen and Matty are in therapy.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:09.75,1:06:12.67,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-搞什么？ -阿爷 亨利·彼得森到底是谁？ \N{\rEng}-Again. -Who's Henry Peterson, Zaydee?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:12.67,1:06:18.00,Default-1,,0,0,0,,{\an7\i1}...珍惜我们的宇宙 不要辜负这150亿年\N{\rEng}{\i1}...the universe that made us or we can squander our 15 billion-year heritage.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:18.02,1:06:20.08,Default-1,,0,0,0,,再买点煎饼粉\N{\rEng}And get some pancake mix.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.11,1:06:22.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要黄盒的 别买橙盒的 都记住了吗？\N{\rEng}Yellow box, not the orange box. You got all that?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.80,1:06:24.18,Default-1,,0,0,0,,记住了\N{\rEng}I got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:24.20,1:06:26.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-要我写下来吗？ -我记得住 \N{\rEng}-Do you need me to write it down? -I got it.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.98,1:06:30.30,Default-1,,0,0,0,,别开车 走路去能醒醒酒\N{\rEng}Don't you think about driving. The walk will sober you up.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.33,1:06:32.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好 好 好\N{\rEng}Yeah, yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:49.74,1:06:52.47,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他去便利店了 一会儿就回来\N{\rEng}He'll be back with some groceries.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.49,1:06:58.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要不今晚一起烤棉花糖？\N{\rEng}Then, how about tonight, we do some s'mores in the fireplace?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:58.36,1:06:59.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,随便\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:59.60,1:07:02.01,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好吧\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.37,1:07:06.05,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他是不是跟你说闹鬼的事了？\N{\rEng}Was he blabbing to you about his ghosts?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.08,1:07:09.55,Default-1,,0,0,0,,阁楼里闹鬼的事？\N{\rEng}The ones that live in the cupola?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:09.90,1:07:11.49,Default-1,,0,0,0,,是呀\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.64,1:07:14.70,Default-1,,0,0,0,,是真的吗？\N{\rEng}Well, are there?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:15.07,1:07:17.40,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你说呢？\N{\rEng}What do you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:17.42,1:07:20.06,Default-1,,0,0,0,,别太信你阿爷\N{\rEng}I wouldn't pay too much attention to Zaydee.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.08,1:07:26.60,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他人不错 就是有时喝得太多\N{\rEng}He's a good man. But, sometimes, well, sometimes, he drinks too much.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.63,1:07:29.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,喝多了就会天马行空 你懂他那一套\N{\rEng}Then he rides his hobby horses. I'm sure you know what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:29.80,1:07:33.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,杰弗里家男孩是谁？\N{\rEng}Who was the Jefferies boy?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:36.40,1:07:41.11,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好吧 小宝 那是件让人心酸的事\N{\rEng}Well...that was a very sad thing, kiddo.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.37,1:07:43.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他住旁边那巷子\N{\rEng}He lived on the next block over,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.80,1:07:49.31,Default-1,,0,0,0,,追球追到马路上结果被车撞了\N{\rEng}and he got hit by a car when he chased a ball into the street.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.33,1:07:52.81,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那是很久前的事儿了\N{\rEng}It happened a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:53.68,1:08:00.80,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要是你爷爷说他提前见过那一幕 他并没有\N{\rEng}And if your grandpa says he saw it before it happened, he's mistaken.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.38,1:08:06.80,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那只是他酒后乱说\N{\rEng}He just drinks too much.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:15.61,1:08:20.29,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要不我帮你送到史坦利奶奶那儿？\N{\rEng}You know, I could take those to Mrs. Stanley if you want.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:20.31,1:08:24.90,Default-1,,0,0,0,,哎呀 你真贴心 维拉看到你肯定特开心\N{\rEng}Oh, that's very thoughtful of you. I bet Vera'd love that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:26.89,1:08:28.48,Default-1,,0,0,0,,简直绝了\N{\rEng}Just wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:28.50,1:08:30.51,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你奶奶真是个烘焙大师\N{\rEng}Your, your grandmother is an artist.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:30.54,1:08:33.31,Default-1,,0,0,0,,谢谢你带来 你主动要来送的吧？\N{\rEng}Thank you for bringing them over. Was that your idea?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:33.33,1:08:35.05,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-说实话哦 -是的 \N{\rEng}-Be honest. -It was.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.07,1:08:37.70,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要喝茶吗？\N{\rEng}Well, can I make you a cup of tea?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.72,1:08:42.39,Default-1,,0,0,0,,其实我不喝茶 有杯牛奶就完美了\N{\rEng}Um, I don't drink tea, but, um, I wouldn't mind a glass of milk.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.67,1:08:46.10,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你奶奶真是个大好人\N{\rEng}Well, your grandmother's a saint.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:46.13,1:08:47.47,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你爷爷呢？\N{\rEng}And what about your granddad?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.47,1:08:49.65,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他背上那东西去检查了吗？\N{\rEng}Did he have that thing on his back looked at?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.68,1:08:52.15,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嗯 医生拿掉了 还做了化验\N{\rEng}Yeah, the, the doctor took it off and had it tested.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.17,1:08:53.85,Default-1,,0,0,0,,全告诉我\N{\rEng}Tell me everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:53.87,1:08:56.55,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不是坏的那种\N{\rEng}It wasn't one of the bad ones.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.57,1:08:58.29,Default-1,,0,0,0,,谢天谢地\N{\rEng}Thank God for that.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.31,1:08:59.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:00.88,1:09:07.60,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他跟奶奶聊那个叫亨利·彼得森的人\N{\rEng}He, um, he was talking to Grandma about someone named Henry Peterson.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:07.62,1:09:08.91,Default-1,,0,0,0,,太惨了\N{\rEng}So awful.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.93,1:09:12.35,Default-1,,0,0,0,,亨利跟你爷爷一样是管账的\N{\rEng}You know, Henry was a bookkeeper, just like your granddad.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.37,1:09:15.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,还接了镇上你阿爷扛不下的活儿...\N{\rEng}He did a lot of the other businesses in town. The ones that your Zaydee didn't do...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.78,1:09:18.17,Default-1,,0,0,0,,到底怎么回事？\N{\rEng}How did it happen?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:19.69,1:09:21.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这种事你还是别听了\N{\rEng}I don't think you want to hear about that stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.77,1:09:26.55,Default-1,,0,0,0,,呃 爷爷说 说那很平和\N{\rEng}Um, w-w-well, Granddad said it was, uh, peaceful.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:26.57,1:09:28.27,Default-1,,0,0,0,,平和？\N{\rEng}Peaceful?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.29,1:09:31.19,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他自尽了 上吊的\N{\rEng}He killed himself. Hung himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:31.21,1:09:34.89,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他老婆跟个刚满十八的小伙子私奔了\N{\rEng}His wife, you see, she ran off with this younger man, barely old enough to vote.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:34.91,1:09:38.46,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她自己都四十多了 你怎么看？\N{\rEng}And she was in her 40s. What do you think of that?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.48,1:09:40.03,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-天哪 -对 可不是 \N{\rEng}-Wow. -Damn right, wow.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:40.05,1:09:43.88,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我还听说...\N{\rEng}And then, I heard that...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.02,1:09:51.18,Default-1,,0,0,0,,学校那边有什么新鲜事？\N{\rEng}What's happening at school?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.20,1:09:53.47,Default-1,,0,0,0,,谁和谁在亲亲啦？\N{\rEng}Who's smooching who?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.50,1:09:58.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,放心说吧 无人能闻得见 我只多留片刻\N{\rEng}"Talk honestly, for no one else hears you and I stay only a minute longer."
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.80,1:10:01.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我是否自相矛盾？\N{\rEng}"Do I contradict myself?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.81,1:10:06.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好吧 那我就自相矛盾\N{\rEng}"Very well then, I contradict myself,"
Dialogue: 0,1:10:06.59,1:10:11.01,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我心疆无限 我包罗万象\N{\rEng}"I am large. I contain multitudes."
Dialogue: 0,1:10:11.03,1:10:13.32,Default-1,,0,0,0,,六年级的最后一堂课上\N{\rEng}On the last day of sixth grade,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.34,1:10:19.54,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那位小清新气息 管不住课堂的理查兹老师\N{\rEng}Miss Richards, a sweet, hippie-dippyish young woman who had no command of discipline
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.56,1:10:24.42,Default-1,,0,0,0,,怕是很快就要被劝退\N{\rEng}and would probably not last long in the public education system,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.44,1:10:32.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,还是在查克班上照念惠特曼《自我之歌》的诗\N{\rEng}tried to recite for Chuck's class some verse of Walt Whitman's "Song of Myself."
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.79,1:10:36.26,Default-1,,0,0,0,,若最初寻我不得 莫失信心\N{\rEng}"Failing to fetch me at first keep encouraged.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:36.28,1:10:40.44,Default-1,,0,0,0,,错过此处 再觅它方\N{\rEng}Missing me one place, search another."
Dialogue: 0,1:10:52.33,1:10:55.14,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这节课还算顺利 对吧？\N{\rEng}That went well, don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,1:10:55.16,1:10:58.83,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嗯 让您为难了\N{\rEng}Yeah, I'm, I'm sorry about that.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:59.39,1:11:09.38,Default-1,,0,0,0,,惠特曼那句“我心疆无限 我包罗万象”是啥意思？\N{\rEng}What does he mean when he says, "I am large, I contain multitudes"?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.40,1:11:11.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你觉得他想表达什么？\N{\rEng}What do you think he means?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.75,1:11:14.09,Default-1,,0,0,0,,包罗他认识的所有人\N{\rEng}All the people he knows.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.11,1:11:15.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,对\N{\rEng}Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:15.88,1:11:19.05,Default-1,,0,0,0,,但也许不止于此\N{\rEng}But maybe he means even more.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:19.08,1:11:22.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,来 过来\N{\rEng}Here. Come here.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.32,1:11:26.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我的两手之间 那里有什么？\N{\rEng}What's in there? Between my hands?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:26.81,1:11:28.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我头\N{\rEng}My brain.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.59,1:11:31.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不 不是这个意思\N{\rEng}No, um, that's not exactly what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:31.81,1:11:37.01,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我是说 在我两手之间 里面装的是什么\N{\rEng}What's in there? Right between my hands right now.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.03,1:11:38.18,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我不知道\N{\rEng}I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:38.20,1:11:41.26,Default-1,,0,0,0,,里面有你认识的所有人吗？\N{\rEng}All the people you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:41.28,1:11:42.80,Default-1,,0,0,0,,有吧\N{\rEng}I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.82,1:11:46.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,就只有你认识的人吗？\N{\rEng}Just the people you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:46.80,1:11:51.46,Default-1,,0,0,0,,里面是你见过的记住的一切\N{\rEng}Everything you see. Everything you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:51.48,1:11:53.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,是整个世界 查克\N{\rEng}The world, Chuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.59,1:11:56.29,Default-1,,0,0,0,,天上的飞机 地上的井盖\N{\rEng}Planes in the sky. Manhole covers in the street.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:56.31,1:11:59.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,年复一年 你脑海中的世界\N{\rEng}Every year that you live, that world inside your head
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.45,1:12:04.13,Default-1,,0,0,0,,会越来越大 越鲜明 越丰富 越复杂\N{\rEng}will get bigger and brighter and more detailed and complex.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:04.15,1:12:07.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你会在脑海中构建城市 国家 大陆\N{\rEng}You will build cities and countries and continents,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:07.80,1:12:12.65,Default-1,,0,0,0,,并用真实和想象的人去充实那里\N{\rEng}and you will fill them with people and faces, real and imagined.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:12.67,1:12:15.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,明白了吗？\N{\rEng}Do you understand?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:15.09,1:12:16.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,别就此止步\N{\rEng}Don't stop there.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.81,1:12:21.24,Default-1,,0,0,0,,把你见过的 认识的\N{\rEng}You fill the whole thing with everyone you ever meet,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.27,1:12:26.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,甚至想象的每个人都给装进去\N{\rEng}everyone you ever know, everyone you ever just imagine.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.78,1:12:29.76,Default-1,,0,0,0,,它就变成了个小宇宙\N{\rEng}It'll be a universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.78,1:12:35.33,Default-1,,0,0,0,,整个宇宙就在我两手之间\N{\rEng}A whole universe right between my hands.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:35.35,1:12:40.85,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你能包罗万象\N{\rEng}You contain multitudes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.18,1:12:42.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那...\N{\rEng}So...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:44.01,1:12:48.26,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那个宇宙会怎样 要是有人...\N{\rEng}what happens to that universe if someone...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:48.28,1:12:50.44,Default-1,,0,0,0,,比如说...\N{\rEng}I don't know,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:50.46,1:12:56.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,在冰面上打滑 冲下高架桥 或者...\N{\rEng}hits a patch of ice and goes off an overpass or...
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.94,1:12:59.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,别太纠结这些\N{\rEng}Don't worry too much about those things.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.81,1:13:05.32,Default-1,,0,0,0,,只要记住 你包罗万象 查克\N{\rEng}Just remember that you contain multitudes, Chuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.34,1:13:08.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这多棒啊\N{\rEng}Isn't that wonderful?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:09.17,1:13:11.45,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好了 就这样 你真是个好孩子\N{\rEng}Now, go on. You were such a good boy.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.48,1:13:15.41,Default-1,,0,0,0,,能教你我很开心\N{\rEng}I've really enjoyed having you in class.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.15,1:13:39.44,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克暑假本来过得挺好 直到八月\N{\rEng}Chuck did enjoy his summer until August,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.46,1:13:42.69,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他阿奶去世了\N{\rEng}when Bubbie died.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:45.40,1:13:48.40,Default-1,,0,0,0,,事情发生在街角的便利店里\N{\rEng}It happened at the grocery store down the street,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.43,1:13:52.15,Default-1,,0,0,0,,公开场合 有点不太体面\N{\rEng}in public, which was a little undignified,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:52.17,1:13:56.25,Default-1,,0,0,0,,至少这种死法能让人安心地说...\N{\rEng}but at least it was the kind of death where people can safely say...
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.28,1:13:59.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,幸好她一生没受什么罪\N{\rEng}Thank God she didn't suffer.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:59.09,1:14:00.56,Default-1,,0,0,0,,至于那句...\N{\rEng}The other standby...
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.58,1:14:02.39,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她一生又长又圆满\N{\rEng}She had a long, full life.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.41,1:14:05.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,就说不准了\N{\rEng}...was more of a gray area.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.18,1:14:09.62,Default-1,,0,0,0,,毕竟她才六十多岁\N{\rEng}Sarah Krantz had yet to reach her mid-60s.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.03,1:14:18.72,Default-1,,0,0,0,,又一次 家里再次陷入彻底的悲伤\N{\rEng}Once more, the house on Pilchard Street was one of unadulterated sadness.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:19.11,1:14:22.80,Default-1,,0,0,0,,阿尔比戴上了黑纱 越发消瘦\N{\rEng}Albie wore his mourning band, and lost weight,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.83,1:14:25.22,Default-1,,0,0,0,,也不再讲笑话了\N{\rEng}and stopped telling his jokes
Dialogue: 0,1:14:25.24,1:14:29.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,比他实际七十岁还显老\N{\rEng}and began to look older than his 70 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:36.35,1:14:39.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-就买这点？ -嗯 \N{\rEng}-That's it? -Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:39.39,1:14:41.98,Default-1,,0,0,0,,一块七毛五\N{\rEng}Buck 75.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:43.39,1:14:50.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,几周前来的那个女士 就是后来去世的那位\N{\rEng}Um, that lady who was in here a few weeks ago, the one who died.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.36,1:14:53.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,事情发生在哪儿？\N{\rEng}Where was she when it happened?
Dialogue: 0,1:14:53.80,1:14:57.38,Default-1,,0,0,0,,小朋友 这话题有点吓人\N{\rEng}That's a little creepy, kid.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:57.41,1:15:00.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她是我奶奶\N{\rEng}She was my grandma.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:01.02,1:15:03.06,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她当时想拿面包\N{\rEng}She was getting a loaf of bread.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:03.08,1:15:07.62,Default-1,,0,0,0,,结果把整排货架都拽倒砸她身上了\N{\rEng}Pulled down almost everything on the shelf when she collapsed.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:07.64,1:15:12.25,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要是我说多了 你别介意\N{\rEng}I'm sorry if that's too much information.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:12.77,1:15:14.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,没事\N{\rEng}Nah.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.51,1:15:18.72,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我早知道了\N{\rEng}I already knew that.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.44,1:16:15.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-别！ -啥？ \N{\rEng}-No! -What?!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:15.18,1:16:20.83,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-走开 快走开 -等下 \N{\rEng}-Get away from there! You get away from there. -What? Hey, hey!
Dialogue: 0,1:16:42.09,1:16:45.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,把锁给我\N{\rEng}Give me that.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.38,1:16:47.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,给我 给我\N{\rEng}Give it to me. Give it to me.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.95,1:16:51.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,抓紧给我\N{\rEng}Give me it.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.59,1:16:57.42,Default-1,,0,0,0,,哦 对不起\N{\rEng}Oh. Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.44,1:16:59.03,Default-1,,0,0,0,,对不起\N{\rEng}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.05,1:17:00.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你没受伤吧\N{\rEng}Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:00.89,1:17:03.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你看到了什么？\N{\rEng}What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:04.50,1:17:06.65,Default-1,,0,0,0,,到底看到了什么？\N{\rEng}What did you see?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.67,1:17:10.61,Default-1,,0,0,0,,对不起 你不能去那里\N{\rEng}I'm sorry. It's just, you can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.63,1:17:13.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,绝不能去那里 小查\N{\rEng}You can't do that, Chucky.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:13.59,1:17:15.26,Default-1,,0,0,0,,绝不能\N{\rEng}You just can't.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:15.28,1:17:17.10,Default-1,,0,0,0,,哦 我真对不起\N{\rEng}Oh, I'm so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.13,1:17:23.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,哦 对不起 真的 真是对不起\N{\rEng}Oh, I'm sorry. I'm so, so sorry. I'm sorry.
