Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.62,1:17:47.21,Note,,0,0,0,,{\move(230,110,244,112)\fs12\i1\1c33AAAAAA\b1\1c&H0E80A2&}舞侠们 来跳舞吧
Dialogue: 0,1:17:45.27,1:17:49.42,Default-1,,0,0,0,,来吧 小老弟 来跳舞吧\N{\rEng}Come on, little brother. Let's dance.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:04.90,1:18:07.66,Default-1,,0,0,0,,舞侠们 舞者们 大家好\N{\rEng}Hello, twirlers, and hello, spinners.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.68,1:18:11.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,哎呦 今年居然有三个男孩 破纪录了\N{\rEng}What do you know? Three boys this year. It's a new record.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.77,1:18:15.15,Default-1,,0,0,0,,小先生们别怕被取笑\N{\rEng}You gentlemen might find yourselves being teased for your new hobby.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.17,1:18:19.02,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我保证 你们是全校最聪明的\N{\rEng}I assure you, you are the smartest young men in the whole school.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.04,1:18:21.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,待会儿你们就明白了\N{\rEng}You'll soon see what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:21.09,1:18:24.11,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不认识我的同学们 我是罗巴赫老师\N{\rEng}For those who don't know me, I am Miss Rohrbacher.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:24.13,1:18:28.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,在女子体育课外 我被尊称为...\N{\rEng}And when I'm not teaching the girls phys-ed,  I am what a few students have called,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:28.79,1:18:31.47,Default-1,,0,0,0,,舞林怪才\N{\rEng}"The Dance Monster."
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.49,1:18:33.30,Default-1,,0,0,0,,没反应？好吧\N{\rEng}Nothing? Alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.32,1:18:37.17,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你们加入的社团堪称学校最牛的\N{\rEng}You have chosen what might be the best club this school has ever had.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:37.19,1:18:40.31,Default-1,,0,0,0,,与女排社团并驾齐驱\N{\rEng}'Cause if we didn't have girls volleyball, we wouldn't have nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.34,1:18:42.35,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不 不 不\N{\rEng}No, no, no.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.37,1:18:47.35,Default-1,,0,0,0,,回来 马尔福同学 你现在归我管了\N{\rEng}Back, Mr. Mulford, you are mine now.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:48.16,1:18:50.67,Default-1,,0,0,0,,华尔兹\N{\rEng}Waltz.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:51.38,1:18:54.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克会跳\N{\rEng}Chuck knew it.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:56.53,1:18:58.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,恰恰舞\N{\rEng}Cha-cha.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.52,1:19:02.44,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克也会跳\N{\rEng}Chuck knew it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.06,1:19:04.81,Default-1,,0,0,0,,摇摆舞\N{\rEng}Swing.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:04.83,1:19:06.59,Default-1,,0,0,0,,三拍步 摇摆步\N{\rEng}Triple step. Rock step.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:06.61,1:19:09.08,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克还会跳\N{\rEng}Chuck knew it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.11,1:19:10.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,三拍步 摇摆步\N{\rEng}Triple step. Rock step.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.80,1:19:14.64,Default-1,,0,0,0,,桑巴舞\N{\rEng}Samba.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.82,1:19:17.13,Default-1,,0,0,0,,没跳过这个\N{\rEng}Don't know that one.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:17.16,1:19:20.39,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他是这小社团里跳的最好的\N{\rEng}He was, by far, the best dancer in the little club.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.41,1:19:24.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,老师常让他和不会跳的女生搭档\N{\rEng}So, Miss Rohrbacher mostly put him with the girls who were clumsy.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:24.98,1:19:30.18,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他明白老师的用意 也乐意帮忙\N{\rEng}He understood she did it to make them better, and he was a good sport about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:30.20,1:19:32.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,快下课前\N{\rEng}Near the end of their two hours, however,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:32.77,1:19:38.10,Default-1,,0,0,0,,舞林怪才才心软 让他和凯特·麦考伊搭档\N{\rEng}The Dance Monster would show mercy and pair him with Cat McCoy,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:38.12,1:19:43.89,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她八年级 也是所有女生里跳得最溜的\N{\rEng}who was an eighth grader and the best dancer of the girls.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.91,1:19:46.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克可没动她的心思\N{\rEng}Chuck didn't expect romance.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.66,1:19:51.64,Default-1,,0,0,0,,卡特确实漂亮 不过也比他高一头\N{\rEng}Cat was not only gorgeous, she was a full foot taller than he was.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.66,1:19:56.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,但他很喜欢和她一起跳 她也有同感\N{\rEng}But he loved to dance with her, and the feeling was mutual.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:56.79,1:19:59.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,...外 二 三 转\N{\rEng}...three. Out, two, three. Switch.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.45,1:20:01.25,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好 停\N{\rEng}And stop.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.27,1:20:03.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,内 二 三 外 二 三\N{\rEng}In, two, three. Out, two, three.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.89,1:20:06.60,Default-1,,0,0,0,,转 换箱步\N{\rEng}Turn. Now box.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.63,1:20:11.92,Default-1,,0,0,0,,一 二 三 一 二 三\N{\rEng}One, two, three. One, two, three.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.94,1:20:14.27,Default-1,,0,0,0,,看 你 们 跳 的 啥\N{\rEng}I don't know what that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:14.29,1:20:15.88,Default-1,,0,0,0,,老 天 呐\N{\rEng}Oh, my God.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.90,1:20:20.61,Default-1,,0,0,0,,算了 自由练十分钟\N{\rEng}Okay, 10 minutes freestyle.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.40,1:20:38.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嘿 瞧好\N{\rEng}Hey. Watch this.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.23,1:20:46.08,Default-1,,0,0,0,,快教我\N{\rEng}Show me how you did that.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.10,1:20:47.56,Default-1,,0,0,0,,看好\N{\rEng}Ready?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:47.58,1:20:50.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,滑 滑 滑\N{\rEng}Slide, slide, slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.87,1:20:52.65,Default-1,,0,0,0,,来试试\N{\rEng}Here, ready?
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.68,1:20:55.13,Default-1,,0,0,0,,来跟我学\N{\rEng}Try it with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.98,1:21:00.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不行 把鞋脱了 穿袜子滑\N{\rEng}Uh, kick off your shoes and do it in your socks.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.98,1:21:03.64,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好 好\N{\rEng}Aye-aye.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.90,1:21:06.28,Default-1,,0,0,0,,滑右脚\N{\rEng}Now, slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.30,1:21:08.27,Default-1,,0,0,0,,滑左脚\N{\rEng}Slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.29,1:21:10.62,Default-1,,0,0,0,,看 你学会了\N{\rEng}Yeah. There you go.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.65,1:21:14.67,Default-1,,0,0,0,,来 让我看看\N{\rEng}Hey! Show me.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:15.00,1:21:19.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,停 滑 停 滑 滑 滑\N{\rEng}Pop. Slide. Pop. Slide. Slide. Slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:19.18,1:21:21.55,Default-1,,0,0,0,,再来次\N{\rEng}Yeah, again.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:21.57,1:21:23.89,Default-1,,0,0,0,,停 滑 停\N{\rEng}Pop. Slide. Pop.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:27.36,1:21:33.13,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那天下课晚了半小时\N{\rEng}Twirlers and Spinners let out half an hour late that day.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.32,1:21:36.26,Default-1,,0,0,0,,刚太酷了 你自己琢磨出来的吗？\N{\rEng}That's so rad. You figured that out by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.28,1:21:41.97,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我就不断回放 反复看 最终学会的\N{\rEng}Well, I just kept rewinding and rewinding 'til I figured it out.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.55,1:21:45.94,Default-1,,0,0,0,,在舞会那天我们一起跳这个吧\N{\rEng}We should do that at the Fling.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.97,1:21:50.23,Default-1,,0,0,0,,呃 别误会 才不是要跟你谈恋爱\N{\rEng}Uh, not as a date or anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:50.25,1:21:52.89,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我跟道奇·温特沃斯在一起\N{\rEng}I'm going out with Dougie Wentworth.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:52.91,1:21:54.48,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你知道吧？\N{\rEng}You know that, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:54.51,1:21:56.36,Default-1,,0,0,0,,知道\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.98,1:22:02.38,Default-1,,0,0,0,,可这不妨碍我们露露绝活\N{\rEng}But that doesn't mean we couldn't show them some cool moves.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:02.40,1:22:04.35,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我超想跳 你呢？\N{\rEng}I really want to. Do you?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:04.38,1:22:06.99,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我 我不确定\N{\rEng}I-I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.01,1:22:09.84,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我太矮了\N{\rEng}I'm a lot shorter.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:09.87,1:22:13.54,Default-1,,0,0,0,,人们会笑话我的\N{\rEng}I think people will laugh.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:27.07,1:22:29.60,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-这管用 -确实管用 \N{\rEng}-That totally works. -It totally does.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:29.63,1:22:31.85,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-确定吗？ -当然确定 \N{\rEng}-Are you sure? -Oh, yeah, I'm sure.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:31.87,1:22:34.89,Default-1,,0,0,0,,感觉很好\N{\rEng}Well, they feel great!
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.21,1:22:37.81,Default-1,,0,0,0,,就是码有点大\N{\rEng}Uh, just a little big.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:39.65,1:22:41.24,Default-1,,0,0,0,,差不多了\N{\rEng}That should be enough.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:41.26,1:22:43.05,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-再塞点 -再塞点 \N{\rEng}-Little more. -Maybe one more.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.08,1:22:45.79,Default-1,,0,0,0,,怎么样？\N{\rEng}How's that?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.23,1:22:49.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,就像溜冰一样\N{\rEng}Floor feels like ice.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:49.45,1:22:52.84,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要是把地板刮花 可要被揍\N{\rEng}You put scratches on that floor, the janitor is gonna beat y...
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.86,1:22:58.04,Default-1,,0,0,0,,蒂米 不会刮花的 他很轻的\N{\rEng}Timmy. There won't be no scratches. He's too light on his feet to leave any.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.19,1:23:01.92,Default-1,,0,0,0,,几乎都对了\N{\rEng}Almost perfect.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.81,1:23:08.51,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这两题再算一遍\N{\rEng}Take another run at these two.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.64,1:23:12.23,Default-1,,0,0,0,,别叹气 你有这方面天赋 知道吗？\N{\rEng}You don't need to sigh. You're good at this, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.25,1:23:13.88,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你真的很出色\N{\rEng}You're really good at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:13.90,1:23:16.45,Default-1,,0,0,0,,好吧 可这也太枯燥了\N{\rEng}Yeah, but it's boring.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.47,1:23:19.23,Default-1,,0,0,0,,枯燥？是说数学吗？\N{\rEng}Boring? What, you mean math?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:19.25,1:23:20.41,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.43,1:23:25.10,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我觉得你下学期课后应该报个数学竞赛社\N{\rEng}I wonder if maybe next semester you might want to try Math League after school.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:25.13,1:23:29.04,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我整个高中都在参加 特有趣\N{\rEng}I did it all high school, in fact, and it was so great.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:29.06,1:23:32.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我现在报的是舞蹈社团\N{\rEng}I'm doing Twirlers and Spinners.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.22,1:23:33.82,Default-1,,0,0,0,,对\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.15,1:23:38.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嘿 先放下笔 先听我说说\N{\rEng}Hey, hey, put that down for a second, will you?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.66,1:23:41.09,Default-1,,0,0,0,,说点数学的事\N{\rEng}Just a little about math.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.12,1:23:44.39,Default-1,,0,0,0,,人们最初都以为它很枯燥\N{\rEng}Because people start out thinking it might be boring,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:44.41,1:23:46.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这就是错在起点\N{\rEng}and that's their first mistake.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:46.98,1:23:50.41,Default-1,,0,0,0,,无论干什么职业 做哪份工作\N{\rEng}It's used in every career, in every job,
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.44,1:23:53.48,Default-1,,0,0,0,,地球上生活的方方面面都离不开它\N{\rEng}in every facet of life on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:53.50,1:23:56.70,Default-1,,0,0,0,,毋庸置疑 就连地球自己也离不开它\N{\rEng}That's a fact. Hell, the planet.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.73,1:23:59.80,Default-1,,0,0,0,,一天到底有多长？\N{\rEng}How do you think we figure out how long a day is?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:59.82,1:24:02.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,谁都知道一天有多长\N{\rEng}Everybody knows how long a day is.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:02.36,1:24:04.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-多长？ -24小时 \N{\rEng}-How long? -Twenty-four hours.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:04.95,1:24:08.41,Default-1,,0,0,0,,大家都说一天有24小时 但这是错的\N{\rEng}People say it's 24 hours, but they're wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:08.43,1:24:13.90,Default-1,,0,0,0,,在恒星日中一天有23小时零56分钟\N{\rEng}There are 23 hours and 56 minutes in a stellar day.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.92,1:24:17.51,Default-1,,0,0,0,,还零几秒钟 数学可以证明\N{\rEng}Plus a few odd seconds. Math proves it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:17.53,1:24:19.95,Default-1,,0,0,0,,怎么知道地球存在多久？\N{\rEng}How do we know how old the Earth is?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:19.97,1:24:23.25,Default-1,,0,0,0,,宇宙存在多久？人类又存在多久？\N{\rEng}How old the universe is, how long people have been here?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.27,1:24:28.00,Default-1,,0,0,0,,又怎么建桥 盖楼 测星距\N{\rEng}Or how to build a bridge or a skyscraper or how far apart the stars are?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:28.02,1:24:29.83,Default-1,,0,0,0,,怎么登月的？\N{\rEng}How did we land on the moon?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:29.85,1:24:34.68,Default-1,,0,0,0,,星星是怎么燃烧的？原子怎么聚变裂变的？\N{\rEng}The stars themselves. Why they burn, why atoms split and fuse,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.71,1:24:37.84,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这些都离不开数学\N{\rEng}and all the rest is just math.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.86,1:24:40.58,Default-1,,0,0,0,,星星本身就是数学产物\N{\rEng}Hey, stars are just math.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:40.61,1:24:42.54,Default-1,,0,0,0,,当你仰望夜空时\N{\rEng}When you look at the night sky,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:42.56,1:24:46.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,看到的是宇宙最壮丽的方程式\N{\rEng}you're seeing the greatest equation in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:46.65,1:24:49.46,Default-1,,0,0,0,,更别说你的舞蹈 那也是数学\N{\rEng}Heck, your dancing, that's math too.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.48,1:24:52.46,Default-1,,0,0,0,,舞蹈的语言到底是什么？\N{\rEng}I mean, what's the language of dance?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:52.48,1:24:54.45,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你怎么学舞步的？\N{\rEng}How do you learn your steps?
Dialogue: 0,1:24:54.48,1:24:58.04,Default-1,,0,0,0,,名字就在那里 叫数拍\N{\rEng}It's even in the name. I mean, they call it "the count."
Dialogue: 0,1:24:58.07,1:24:59.68,Default-1,,0,0,0,,一 二 三 四\N{\rEng}One and two and three and four.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:59.70,1:25:02.51,Default-1,,0,0,0,,华尔兹呢？一 二 三 一 二 三\N{\rEng}What's a waltz? One, two, three, one, two, three.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:02.53,1:25:05.69,Default-1,,0,0,0,,全是数字 都是数学\N{\rEng}Just numbers, just math.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:05.71,1:25:07.80,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不仅如此\N{\rEng}And more than that,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:07.83,1:25:10.61,Default-1,,0,0,0,,数学可以是门艺术\N{\rEng}there's an art to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:10.63,1:25:15.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我干的活儿 你看这堆文件 这些档案\N{\rEng}What I do, all these files here, all these folders,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.59,1:25:18.32,Default-1,,0,0,0,,记录的都是人们的生活\N{\rEng}these are all people's lives.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:18.35,1:25:20.97,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他们每个选择\N{\rEng}Every choice they made.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.99,1:25:23.39,Default-1,,0,0,0,,去年 过去十年\N{\rEng}Last year, last 10 years.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:23.41,1:25:25.54,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他们在意的一切\N{\rEng}Everything that's important to them.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:25.56,1:25:28.71,Default-1,,0,0,0,,所有缺点 嗜好和梦想\N{\rEng}Every weakness they have, every vice, every dream,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:28.73,1:25:32.67,Default-1,,0,0,0,,全都体现在数字里\N{\rEng}it's all here in numbers.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.69,1:25:35.15,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要是哪个外行进来 生搬硬算\N{\rEng}Some schmuck comes in, takes those numbers,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:35.17,1:25:39.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,缺了艺术感 就能害人丢了房子\N{\rEng}does the math without artistry, someone loses their house.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.18,1:25:43.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,而我注入一丝艺术匠心\N{\rEng}I take those numbers, do a little art,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.18,1:25:45.60,Default-1,,0,0,0,,便能救人于难\N{\rEng}I save someone's life.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.62,1:25:47.25,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这就是会计的魅力\N{\rEng}That's what I do.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:47.27,1:25:51.05,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这就是会计的意义\N{\rEng}That's what accounting is.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:51.08,1:25:55.11,Default-1,,0,0,0,,也许他们该教这些有趣的\N{\rEng}Well, maybe they should teach that, the cool stuff,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.13,1:25:58.30,Default-1,,0,0,0,,别教枯燥的\N{\rEng}and not just all the boring stuff.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.33,1:25:59.46,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rEng}Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:06.77,1:26:09.71,Default-1,,0,0,0,,数学可不止这些\N{\rEng}Math is something else too.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:09.73,1:26:14.54,Default-1,,0,0,0,,像统计学 概率学\N{\rEng}Some math, math that's called statistics or probability,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.56,1:26:18.03,Default-1,,0,0,0,,可以未卜先知\N{\rEng}it can tell you stuff about your future.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:18.49,1:26:21.56,Default-1,,0,0,0,,比方说\N{\rEng}It could tell you, for example,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.59,1:26:25.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你进职业球队的几率\N{\rEng}you're more likely to be drafted by a major league sports team
Dialogue: 0,1:26:25.65,1:26:29.61,Default-1,,0,0,0,,大过靠跳舞谋生\N{\rEng}than to make a real living as a dancer.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.04,1:26:35.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,大家都爱看跳舞 没错\N{\rEng}The world loves dancers, it truly does.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:35.80,1:26:38.70,Default-1,,0,0,0,,可社会更需要会计师\N{\rEng}But it needs accountants,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.72,1:26:43.84,Default-1,,0,0,0,,需求大所以机会也多\N{\rEng}so there's much more demand, so there's much more opportunity.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:44.02,1:26:48.05,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我知道这话扎心 但这就是事实\N{\rEng}I know that might hurt, but it's the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:48.07,1:26:53.06,Default-1,,0,0,0,,数学不会撒谎 它只讲事实\N{\rEng}Math is truth. It won't lie to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:53.08,1:26:58.81,Default-1,,0,0,0,,数学不掺感情 它就是这么纯粹\N{\rEng}It doesn't factor in your preferences. It's pure that way.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:59.00,1:27:02.56,Default-1,,0,0,0,,数学能做很多事\N{\rEng}Math can do a lot of things.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:03.00,1:27:06.38,Default-1,,0,0,0,,数学可以是门艺术\N{\rEng}Math can be art.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.40,1:27:08.86,Default-1,,0,0,0,,但数学可不会撒谎\N{\rEng}But it can't lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.88,1:27:09.88,Default-1,,0,0,0,,所以...\N{\rEng}So...
Dialogue: 0,1:27:11.39,1:27:15.56,Default-1,,0,0,0,,再把那两题重算一遍吧\N{\rEng}take another run at those two because, Chucko,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.58,1:27:18.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,小查 你很出色\N{\rEng}you are good.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:18.54,1:27:22.99,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你有 艺术细胞\N{\rEng}You... have art in you.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.02,1:28:06.17,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嘿！你今天超好看的！\N{\rEng}Hey! You look great!
Dialogue: 0,1:28:06.19,1:28:09.26,Default-1,,0,0,0,,谢谢 你也是\N{\rEng}Thanks. Uh, you too.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:10.33,1:28:12.31,Default-1,,0,0,0,,想不想给他们露两手？\N{\rEng}Wanna show 'em how it's done?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:12.33,1:28:19.02,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这个 我不 我 我可能扭到脚了\N{\rEng}Uh, I don't know. I kinda, um...I kinda hurt my leg.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.35,1:28:21.09,Default-1,,0,0,0,,真的假的？\N{\rEng}You hurt your leg?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:21.11,1:28:24.66,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要不 要不 等首更好的歌吧？\N{\rEng}Maybe, maybe let's, let's wait for a better song.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:45.80,1:28:47.78,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嘿 小子\N{\rEng}Hey, kiddo.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.15,1:28:49.85,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嘿\N{\rEng}Hey.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.24,1:28:55.18,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我以为你今晚要大放异彩呢\N{\rEng}Thought you were gonna tear it up tonight.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:55.21,1:28:57.36,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我 我也不知道\N{\rEng}I don't, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.38,1:28:59.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,鞋子怪怪的\N{\rEng}My shoes feel all funny,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.55,1:29:03.47,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我 我脚扭了\N{\rEng}and... I hurt my leg.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.82,1:29:06.67,Default-1,,0,0,0,,哦 你脚扭了？\N{\rEng}Oh, you hurt your leg?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:06.69,1:29:08.02,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嗯\N{\rEng}Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.21,1:29:11.23,Default-1,,0,0,0,,真替你可惜\N{\rEng}I'm sorry to hear that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:11.35,1:29:12.98,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你一个人来的？\N{\rEng}So, you came stag, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:13.00,1:29:15.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-啥？-没带约会对象？ \N{\rEng}-Hmm? -No date.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:15.60,1:29:17.29,Default-1,,0,0,0,,没 我\N{\rEng}Nah, I...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.31,1:29:22.95,Default-1,,0,0,0,,情况会变的 相信我 迟早会变 再等等\N{\rEng}That'll change. Believe me, it'll change. Just give it some time.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.97,1:29:24.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,舞池里这些...\N{\rEng}None of this, none of...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:24.79,1:29:27.65,Default-1,,0,0,0,,舞池里这些都不重要\N{\rEng}None of that out there really means anything.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.67,1:29:33.44,Default-1,,0,0,0,,跳得怎样 都只是热身和演习 别把它当真\N{\rEng}It's all just, just a scrimmage. Just a practice.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:34.50,1:29:36.83,Default-1,,0,0,0,,嘿 这首正好 来跳吧\N{\rEng}Hey, this is perfect. Come on.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:36.85,1:29:39.18,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不行 我...\N{\rEng}Nah, I'm still, uh...
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.20,1:29:40.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我脚还怪怪的\N{\rEng}My leg's still wonky.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:40.78,1:29:43.66,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克 得了吧 让我们炸翻全场\N{\rEng}Chuck, come on. We're gonna blow the roof off.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.68,1:29:45.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,对不起\N{\rEng}I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:45.90,1:29:48.27,Default-1,,0,0,0,,真的很痛\N{\rEng}It really hurts.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.92,1:30:07.69,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我从八岁就开始跳舞 又教体育\N{\rEng}You know, I've been dancing since I was eight, and I teach PE,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.71,1:30:10.12,Default-1,,0,0,0,,看过不少孩子受伤后的样子\N{\rEng}and I've seen when my kids get hurt.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.14,1:30:12.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他们走路都不一样了\N{\rEng}I see how their walk changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:12.66,1:30:14.57,Default-1,,0,0,0,,站姿也怪\N{\rEng}I see how their posture changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:14.60,1:30:17.72,Default-1,,0,0,0,,说句实话 在我看来...\N{\rEng}And don't mind me saying, but you look...
Dialogue: 0,1:30:18.25,1:30:21.40,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克 你看上去好好的\N{\rEng}Well, you look fine to me, Chuck.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:21.42,1:30:26.06,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我没逼你非得跟她跳 决定权在你\N{\rEng}I'm not saying that you have to dance with the girl. It's up to you.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:26.09,1:30:31.20,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我只想说 不管跳不跳 别说谎\N{\rEng}I'm just saying dance or no dance, you don't have to lie.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.22,1:30:34.65,Default-1,,0,0,0,,跟她实话实说\N{\rEng}Tell her the truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.47,1:30:38.70,Default-1,,0,0,0,,她会理解的\N{\rEng}She can take it.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:50.98,1:31:54.72,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-准备好了吗？ -嗯 来跳吧 \N{\rEng}-You ready? -Yeah. Let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.08,1:34:20.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,再跳一遍！再跳一遍！\N{\rEng}One more time! One more time!
Dialogue: 0,1:34:20.87,1:34:28.42,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他们年纪虽小 却足够聪明知道何时收场\N{\rEng}They may have been young, but they were smart enough to know when to quit.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:33.93,1:34:35.39,Default-1,,0,0,0,,谢谢大家\N{\rEng}Thank you, guys.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:35.41,1:34:40.70,Default-1,,0,0,0,,在他39岁因脑瘤早逝前六个月\N{\rEng}Six months before he died of a brain tumor at the unfair age of 39,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:40.72,1:34:44.44,Default-1,,0,0,0,,趁头脑还算清楚\N{\rEng}and while his mind was still working, mostly,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.46,1:34:50.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他跟妻子珍妮坦白了手背上疤的来历\N{\rEng}Chuck told his wife the truth about the scar on the back of his hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:50.77,1:34:52.62,Default-1,,0,0,0,,最开始交往时\N{\rEng}When they'd first started dating,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:52.64,1:34:56.25,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他说这疤是那晚舞会后\N{\rEng}he told her he'd gotten it from a boy named Doug Wentworth,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.27,1:35:01.15,Default-1,,0,0,0,,舞伴凯特的男友温特沃斯因为吃醋\N{\rEng}who was pissed about him dancing with his girlfriend at a middle school formal
Dialogue: 0,1:35:01.17,1:35:04.53,Default-1,,0,0,0,,把他推到围栏上铁丝划的\N{\rEng}and pushed him into a chain link fence outside the gym.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:04.55,1:35:07.71,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这疤我没说真话\N{\rEng}I lied about that, though.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:09.05,1:35:14.68,Default-1,,0,0,0,,哇 你还是这么神秘\N{\rEng}Oh, my. A man of secrets, even still.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:16.06,1:35:17.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,亲爱的 怎么弄的？\N{\rEng}What happened, love?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:17.89,1:35:20.56,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那晚舞跳完\N{\rEng}When our fabulous dance was over, I...
Dialogue: 0,1:35:20.58,1:35:23.74,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我全身又汗又热\N{\rEng}I was sweaty and I was so hot.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:23.76,1:35:25.92,Default-1,,0,0,0,,脸都热得通红\N{\rEng}I-I felt like my cheeks were gonna catch fire.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.95,1:35:27.19,Default-1,,0,0,0,,跳的太好了\N{\rEng}You were great.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.22,1:35:29.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-谢谢 -真是个大明星啊 \N{\rEng}-Thank you. -What a star.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.90,1:35:33.49,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我那时只想逃离灯光\N{\rEng}All I wanted in that moment was just darkness,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:33.51,1:35:39.95,Default-1,,0,0,0,,吹吹凉风 一个人呆会儿\N{\rEng}cool air, and to be by myself.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:42.00,1:35:45.72,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那晚天空繁星闪烁\N{\rEng}There were millions of stars that night.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:45.74,1:35:47.59,Default-1,,0,0,0,,千万星辰\N{\rEng}Millions of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.61,1:35:50.33,Default-1,,0,0,0,,千层万叠\N{\rEng}And millions more behind them.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.35,1:35:55.29,Default-1,,0,0,0,,也许 嗯 它们只是天文数字\N{\rEng}And sure, m-may... Yeah, maybe they were just math.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:55.31,1:35:57.92,Default-1,,0,0,0,,却好像在翩翩起舞\N{\rEng}But they also danced.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:57.94,1:36:02.38,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我知道 因为那一瞬我看见了\N{\rEng}I know 'cause I saw one of them.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:02.88,1:36:06.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我那时想 宇宙广阔无限\N{\rEng}And I remember thinking, the universe is large
Dialogue: 0,1:36:06.54,1:36:09.06,Default-1,,0,0,0,,宇宙包罗万象\N{\rEng}and, and it contains multitudes,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:09.09,1:36:13.46,Default-1,,0,0,0,,也包含了我\N{\rEng}but it-it also contains me.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:13.59,1:36:19.67,Default-1,,0,0,0,,而在那一刻 我真觉得自己很精彩\N{\rEng}And in this moment...I am wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:19.69,1:36:22.92,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我理应拥有这份精彩\N{\rEng}And I have a right to be wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.95,1:36:24.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,啊\N{\rEng}Oh!
Dialogue: 0,1:36:27.78,1:36:31.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,干嘛为这事撒谎 小傻瓜\N{\rEng}Why lie about that, silly?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:31.18,1:36:35.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你真是个奇妙的存在 亲爱的\N{\rEng}You're a strange wonder, my dear.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:35.09,1:36:41.99,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他没再多说 因为那道疤另有深意\N{\rEng}He doesn't offer more because the scar was important for another reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:42.01,1:36:45.17,Default-1,,0,0,0,,是他讲不完的故事的一环\N{\rEng}It was part of a story he couldn't tell,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.19,1:36:50.18,Default-1,,0,0,0,,其中有他长大的那幢维多利亚老宅\N{\rEng}even though there was now an apartment building on the site of the Victorian house
Dialogue: 0,1:36:50.20,1:36:53.74,Default-1,,0,0,0,,尽管早拆了盖楼了\N{\rEng}where he had done most of his growing up.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.76,1:36:57.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那幢闹鬼的维多利亚老宅\N{\rEng}The haunted Victorian house.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:57.99,1:36:59.86,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不知道\N{\rEng}No reason.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.82,1:37:03.10,Default-1,,0,0,0,,就是心血来潮吧\N{\rEng}Funny thinking, I guess.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:03.12,1:37:07.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这疤意义非凡 他也尽力讲得加料\N{\rEng}The scar meant more, so he had made it more.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.65,1:37:12.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,可讲得总没有它真正的意义深\N{\rEng}He just couldn't make it as much more as it really was.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.09,1:37:14.29,Default-1,,0,0,0,,讲得还有点糊涂\N{\rEng}That made little sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:14.32,1:37:18.69,Default-1,,0,0,0,,但随着脑癌细胞的疯狂进攻\N{\rEng}But as the glioblastoma continued its blitzkrieg,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:18.71,1:37:24.91,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他那快散架的大脑最多也只能讲到这样\N{\rEng}it was the best his disintegrating mind could manage.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.86,1:37:58.64,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克的爷爷 他的阿爷\N{\rEng}Chuck's grandpa, his Zaydee,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:58.66,1:38:04.47,Default-1,,0,0,0,,在那场秋季舞会五年后 因心脏病发作去世\N{\rEng}died of a heart attack five years after the Fall Fling dance.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:04.49,1:38:06.92,Default-1,,0,0,0,,事发时查克读高二\N{\rEng}Chuck was a junior in high school
Dialogue: 0,1:38:06.94,1:38:08.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,是乐队主唱\N{\rEng}singing in a band and
Dialogue: 0,1:38:08.76,1:38:12.98,Default-1,,0,0,0,,正在台上像摇滚巨星一样跳得带劲儿\N{\rEng}dancing like Jagger during the instrumental breaks.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:13.00,1:38:16.22,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他自己都安排妥当了\N{\rEng}He made all the arrangements himself.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:16.24,1:38:18.12,Default-1,,0,0,0,,几周前\N{\rEng}Came in a few weeks ago
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.14,1:38:20.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,还特地来馆里再确认一遍\N{\rEng}just to make sure everything was to the letter,
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.75,1:38:23.01,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我还纳闷呢\N{\rEng}which I thought was strange.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.31,1:38:25.39,Default-1,,0,0,0,,很少有人这么上心\N{\rEng}Not many people bother to do that.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.41,1:38:30.01,Default-1,,0,0,0,,大多数人只来一趟定好流程\N{\rEng}Most people, they come here once to set it all up.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.25,1:38:33.41,Default-1,,0,0,0,,办好手续就不再来了\N{\rEng}They aren't anxious to come back again.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.43,1:38:40.07,Default-1,,0,0,0,,再见到那人 都是穿着体面衣服躺那儿 懂吧\N{\rEng}Next time I see 'em, they're in their Sunday best, if you get me.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.09,1:38:44.18,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他人特好 也是我多年的好友\N{\rEng}He was a great man and a good friend.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:44.67,1:38:47.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他为我们做账整整二十三年了\N{\rEng}He's been doing our books for 23 years
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.78,1:38:53.04,Default-1,,0,0,0,,账做得稳 多次税务检查都帮我们顺利过关\N{\rEng}and saved our skin more than once when the tax man was coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:53.81,1:38:56.34,Default-1,,0,0,0,,要现在给你结账吗？\N{\rEng}So, do I owe you any money?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:56.37,1:38:57.94,Default-1,,0,0,0,,一分都不用\N{\rEng}Not a penny.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:57.96,1:39:03.70,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他那次来就把钱全给结清了\N{\rEng}He took care of that too. Settled his tab that same visit.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:03.75,1:39:05.50,Default-1,,0,0,0,,听我说\N{\rEng}You know...
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.98,1:39:08.05,Default-1,,0,0,0,,最离奇的是\N{\rEng}the strangest thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.07,1:39:11.40,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这事儿很怪 可别觉得我扯\N{\rEng}And this will sound strange, so bear with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:11.42,1:39:13.05,Default-1,,0,0,0,,说来话长\N{\rEng}See,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:13.05,1:39:18.11,Default-1,,0,0,0,,年轻时我曾想当电视上天气预报员\N{\rEng}I, uh, dreamed of being a television weatherman in my salad days
Dialogue: 0,1:39:18.13,1:39:20.85,Default-1,,0,0,0,,也许能成全国台的\N{\rEng}with maybe one of the networks.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:20.87,1:39:22.98,Default-1,,0,0,0,,最终没成\N{\rEng}Wasn't in the cards for me.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:23.31,1:39:28.12,Default-1,,0,0,0,,倒是去地方台待过一个夏天\N{\rEng}But I did spend a summer at WKNB.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.14,1:39:32.95,Default-1,,0,0,0,,在那儿 有个同事号称能\N{\rEng}Well, there was a guy at KNB who they said
Dialogue: 0,1:39:32.97,1:39:38.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,不用雷达就能提前两周感知风暴\N{\rEng}could feel a storm coming two solid weeks away without the radar.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.96,1:39:40.69,Default-1,,0,0,0,,有第六感\N{\rEng}Had a sixth sense.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:40.72,1:39:43.04,Default-1,,0,0,0,,简直了\N{\rEng}Damnedest thing I ever saw.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:43.06,1:39:45.35,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他会露出一种神情\N{\rEng}Uh, used to make this face,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:45.37,1:39:48.83,Default-1,,0,0,0,,当别人说要出远门\N{\rEng}this face when people talked about their travel plans,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.85,1:39:50.92,Default-1,,0,0,0,,然后他洞察出什么后\N{\rEng}if he knew something they didn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:50.94,1:39:55.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那神情不笑不乐\N{\rEng}Not... not a smile, per se. No joy in it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:55.95,1:40:00.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,就一脸 我全知道的样子\N{\rEng}Just a... knowing.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:00.39,1:40:03.31,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我管那叫 预报员天眼\N{\rEng}"Weatherman Stare," I called it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:03.34,1:40:06.01,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我可没那本事\N{\rEng}And I didn't have it, not me.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:06.04,1:40:10.89,Default-1,,0,0,0,,所以我在这行 而不是那行\N{\rEng}So, I'm here, not there.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:11.13,1:40:16.60,Default-1,,0,0,0,,你爷爷来时也带着同样的神情\N{\rEng}Your granddad had that same face when he was in here.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:16.62,1:40:20.73,Default-1,,0,0,0,,像是 他早料到要下雨\N{\rEng}Like... he knew it was gonna rain.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:20.75,1:40:25.48,Default-1,,0,0,0,,而我只是个卖他伞的人\N{\rEng}And I was just a guy selling him an umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:25.50,1:40:27.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,那就是预报员天眼\N{\rEng}Weatherman Stare.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:27.80,1:40:30.37,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我敢打包票\N{\rEng}I'm sure of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:30.85,1:40:33.11,Default-1,,0,0,0,,太离谱了\N{\rEng}The strangest thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:34.20,1:40:36.45,Default-1,,0,0,0,,爷爷阿尔比把一切家当都留给了他\N{\rEng}Albie left him everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:36.47,1:40:40.09,Default-1,,0,0,0,,这足够支付他的大学学费\N{\rEng}More than enough to pay for his college education.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:40.11,1:40:43.45,Default-1,,0,0,0,,再后来 他把那幢维多利亚老宅卖了\N{\rEng}And later on, the sale of the Victorian
Dialogue: 0,1:40:43.47,1:40:45.43,Default-1,,0,0,0,,用这笔钱买了\N{\rEng}paid for the house he and Ginny moved into
Dialogue: 0,1:40:45.46,1:40:50.46,Default-1,,0,0,0,,和他妻子珍妮度蜜月后住的新家\N{\rEng}after their honeymoon in the Catskills.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:50.48,1:40:56.25,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他铁了心不去奥马哈和外公外婆一起住\N{\rEng}He flatly refused to move to Omaha to live with his mother's parents.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:56.27,1:40:58.16,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-听着 我真的很爱你们... -他这样说 \N{\rEng}-Look, I love you guys... -He said.
Dialogue: 0,1:40:58.18,1:41:01.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,...但我在这里长大的 也想在这待到上大学\N{\rEng}...but this is where I grew up and want to stay till college.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:01.66,1:41:03.69,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我都17了 不是小孩子了\N{\rEng}I'm 17. I'm not a baby.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:03.71,1:41:09.65,Default-1,,0,0,0,,于是 早已退休的老两口 住进那幢维多利亚老宅\N{\rEng}So, they, both long retired, came to him and stayed in the Victorian
Dialogue: 0,1:41:09.67,1:41:12.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,陪查克二十多个月\N{\rEng}for the 20-odd months before Chuck went off
Dialogue: 0,1:41:12.54,1:41:16.84,Default-1,,0,0,0,,直到他去伊利诺伊大学\N{\rEng}to the University of Illinois.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:16.92,1:41:21.60,Default-1,,0,0,0,,可他们没赶上参加葬礼\N{\rEng}They weren't able to be there for the funeral, however.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:21.63,1:41:24.28,Default-1,,0,0,0,,葬礼办得很快 正如阿尔比所愿\N{\rEng}It happened fast, as Albie had wanted,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:24.30,1:41:29.26,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他外公外婆在奥马哈还有一些事要收尾\N{\rEng}and his mom's folks had loose ends to tie up in Omaha.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:29.29,1:41:32.89,Default-1,,0,0,0,,说实话 查克并不怎么想他们\N{\rEng}Chuck didn't really miss them, if he was honest.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:32.91,1:41:40.75,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他跟他阿爷一样 最讨厌瞎折腾 也受不了人多\N{\rEng}His Zaydee hated a fuss almost as much as he hated a crowd.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:41.65,1:41:44.47,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他们来的前一天\N{\rEng}A day before they were scheduled to arrive,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:44.49,1:41:46.84,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克才拆开\N{\rEng}Chuck finally opened the envelope
Dialogue: 0,1:41:46.87,1:41:51.12,Default-1,,0,0,0,,放玄关桌上的那大信封\N{\rEng}that had been sitting on the table in the front hall.
Dialogue: 0,1:41:51.14,1:41:53.87,Default-1,,0,0,0,,信封是来自山姆·雅伯勒\N{\rEng}It was from Sam Yarborough,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:53.89,1:41:57.96,Default-1,,0,0,0,,亚伯勒殡仪馆的老板兼首席殡葬师\N{\rEng}owner and chief undertaker at Yarborough Funeral Home,
Dialogue: 0,1:41:57.98,1:42:04.70,Default-1,,0,0,0,,里面装着阿尔比·克兰兹的个人物品\N{\rEng}and inside were Albie Krantz's personal effects.
Dialogue: 0,1:43:58.96,1:44:03.17,Default-1,,0,0,0,,在这屋里 查克爷爷见过杰弗里家那男孩\N{\rEng}In this room, Chuck's grandpa had seen the Jefferies boy,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:03.19,1:44:06.84,Default-1,,0,0,0,,被车撞得血肉模糊\N{\rEng}body broken by the car.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:06.87,1:44:11.23,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他见过亨利·彼得森吊在天花板上\N{\rEng}He'd seen Henry Peterson hanging from the ceiling.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:11.25,1:44:14.51,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他还见过他妻子躺在地上断了气\N{\rEng}He'd seen his own wife lying dead.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:14.53,1:44:16.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,查克想\N{\rEng}And likely, Chuck supposed,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:16.95,1:44:20.97,Default-1,,0,0,0,,也许就在那晚他偷钥匙的时候\N{\rEng}perhaps the night Chuck had stolen his keys,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:20.99,1:44:25.33,Default-1,,0,0,0,,阿尔比还看见自己摔倒在地\N{\rEng}Albie had even seen himself crumpled to the floor,
Dialogue: 0,1:44:25.35,1:44:28.77,Default-1,,0,0,0,,死死抓着胳膊\N{\rEng}still clutching his upper arm.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:28.79,1:44:32.55,Default-1,,0,0,0,,“这就是等待”他说\N{\rEng}"It's the waiting," he'd said.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:32.57,1:44:35.64,Default-1,,0,0,0,,“这是最难熬的”\N{\rEng}"That's the hard part."
Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.66,1:44:39.95,Default-1,,0,0,0,,现在轮到查克自己的煎熬了\N{\rEng}Now Chuck's own waiting would begin.
Dialogue: 0,1:44:39.97,1:44:42.91,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他到底要等多久？\N{\rEng}How long would that wait be?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:42.93,1:44:48.86,Default-1,,0,0,0,,病床上那个人到底多少岁？\N{\rEng}Exactly how old was the man in the hospital bed?
Dialogue: 0,1:44:51.98,1:44:57.18,Default-1,,0,0,0,,看不见的监护仪发出最后一声“哔”\N{\rEng}There was a final bip from the unseen monitor
Dialogue: 0,1:44:57.20,1:45:00.60,Default-1,,0,0,0,,然后也随之消失\N{\rEng}and then that was gone too.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:01.99,1:45:07.63,Default-1,,0,0,0,,他不像电影里那样慢慢淡去\N{\rEng}The man did not fade, as ghostly apparitions did in the movies.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:07.65,1:45:10.28,Default-1,,0,0,0,,就直接不见了\N{\rEng}He was just gone.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:10.30,1:45:15.08,Default-1,,0,0,0,,仿佛他从未出现过\N{\rEng}Insisting he had never been there in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:15.53,1:45:17.93,Default-1,,0,0,0,,-那不可能... -查克想 \N{\rEng}-He wasn't... -Chuck thinks.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.95,1:45:20.86,Default-1,,0,0,0,,...我偏不信\N{\rEng}...and I will insist he wasn't.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:20.88,1:45:26.52,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我会痛痛快快地活 直到最后一刻\N{\rEng}And I will live my life until my life runs out.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.54,1:45:29.28,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我很精彩\N{\rEng}I am wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.85,1:45:33.38,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我配得上这份精彩\N{\rEng}I deserve to be wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.24,1:45:37.62,Default-1,,0,0,0,,我包罗万象\N{\rEng}And I contain multitudes.
Dialogue: 0,1:46:03.09,1:46:05.68,Note,,0,0,0,,{\pos(192,134)\1c&HA2B7C1&\fs11\fsp4}导演及影片编剧\N{\fs14\fsp1}迈克·弗拉纳根
